INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8,1,'2010-01-22 01:43:09','2010-01-22 05:43:09','Dear MCS parents,   This Saturday we will have our first <strong>Parent Assembly (家長大會).</strong> <strong></strong> <strong>The following is the meeting agenda starting from 1:45pm</strong> 1.  Introduction of new PTA chair - Mr. Jim Yang,\r\n\r\n楊理鈞, class representatives, and new parents that just join MCS\r\n\r\n2. Introduction of school staff - Principal\r\n\r\n3. Overview of school mission &amp; status - Principal\r\n\r\n4. Detail presentation of school status, budget, and new policies - Staff\r\n\r\n5. Walk-ins\r\n\r\nThis meeting offers you the opportunity to understand school operation and to provide your inputs. Please come and show your support.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\n\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Parent Assembly Meeting - 9/26/09 1:45pm at Parents Lounge (room 2423/2425)',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-parent-assembly-meeting-92609-145pm-at-parents-lounge-room-24232425','','','2010-01-22 01:43:09','2010-01-22 05:43:09','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=8',0,'post','',0),(9,1,'2010-01-22 01:42:40','2010-01-22 05:42:40','','MCS Parent Assembly Meeting - 9/26/09 1:45pm at Parents Lounge (room 2423/2425)',0,'','inherit','open','open','','8-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:42:40','2010-01-22 05:42:40','',8,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=9',0,'revision','',0),(10,1,'2010-01-22 01:44:19','2010-01-22 05:44:19','Dear MCS parents,   This Saturday we will have our first <strong>Parent Assembly (家長大會).</strong> <strong></strong> <strong>The following is the meeting agenda starting from 1:45pm</strong> 1.  Introduction of new PTA chair - Mr. Jim Yang,\n\n楊理鈞, class representatives, and new parents that just join MCS\n\n2. Introduction of school staff - Principal\n\n3. Overview of school mission &amp; status - Principal\n\n4. Detail presentation of school status, budget, and new policies - Staff\n\n5. Walk-ins\n\nThis meeting offers you the opportunity to understand school operation and to provide your inputs. Please come and show your support.\n\nAlex Tang\n\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Parent Assembly Meeting - 9/26/09 1:45pm at Parents Lounge (room 2423/2425)',0,'','inherit','open','open','','8-autosave','','','2010-01-22 01:44:19','2010-01-22 05:44:19','',8,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=10',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2010-01-22 01:38:46','2010-01-22 05:38:46','MCS parents,\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">9/22, Tuesday 7pm </span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: DFKai-SB; color: #ff0000;\" lang=\"ZH-TW\">中華民國文化訪問團</span><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> will perform at </span><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: DFKai-SB; color: #ff0000;\">West Bloomfield High School Auditorium</span>. This Saturday is your last chance to buy tickets at our school. Part of the ticket income from this concert will be donated to help the Taiwan people suffered from 8/8 Flood, part of the income will be used to help local Chinese school education for your kids. I strongly encourage you to participate in this wonderful event. It\'s going to be one of these unforgettable experience in your lifetime, well, at least this is how I feel.\r\n\r\nGreat News! -------- <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">MCS has a new website</span> and a new webmaster - Thanks to the great effort from our Pre-K parent Mr Steven Lien. The URL to our school can be accessed in any of the following three ways:\r\n1.  <a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.netfirms.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.michiganchineseschool.netfirms.com</a>\r\n2.  <a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\r\n3.  <a href=\"../../\" target=\"_blank\">michiganchineseschool.org</a>.\r\n\r\nPlease visit the site and provide us your inputs. More diversified information and articles will be uploaded from time to time. We are also developing Blog function for each class so teachers and students, parents may develop more <span>communication</span> by using internet.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">This Saturday is the beginning week for our extra curricular activities</span>. Classroom 2444 is for Lego Robotics and room 2442 is for Arts. There are still spaces in the extra curriculum classes. Don\'t miss this opportunity! We will also start to register the English Writing class. Alex Wan will provide more details at school.\r\n\r\nPre-K and 1st grade parents, please note that classroom has been exchanged between this two classes.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff4040;\">9/26 is our first Parent  Assembly Meeting</span>. Please attend to show your support to the school. Information regarding to the student registration, new scholarship system, website..etc. will be presented. Don\'t miss the opportunity to participate.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">For parents elected as class representative, we will meet at parent/staff room (2423/2425) this Saturday 1:45pm to elect PTA chair</span>. Your attendance is critical to future school operation.\r\n\r\nBest regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','School communication - New website - Last call for ticket sale (9/22 concert)',0,'','publish','closed','open','','school-communication-new-website-last-call-for-ticket-sale-922-concert','','','2010-01-22 01:38:46','2010-01-22 05:38:46','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=6',0,'post','',0),(7,1,'2010-01-22 01:38:10','2010-01-22 05:38:10','','School communication - New website - Last call for ticket sale (9/22 concert)',0,'','inherit','open','open','','6-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:38:10','2010-01-22 05:38:10','',6,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2010-01-22 01:45:01','2010-01-22 05:45:01','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nWe held our first Parents Assembly last Saturday. About 40 parents attended this meeting. School staff presented school status and 2009-2010 budget. This semester we registered 24 new students and 84 old students. Our enrollment rate reversed the declining trend in the past few years and added 3 more students comparing to last fall. Thanks for your effort in introducing our school to your friends. This Saturday we will issue the recruiting award check at parents lounge (room 2423/2425).\r\n\r\nLast Saturday we found a cell phone at women\'s restroom opposite to room 2419. You may come to the Parent lounge this Saturday to claim it if you are the owner.\r\n\r\nWe will pass out moon cakes to every student this Saturday to celebrate <span>Chinese</span> Moon Festival. We will also show a video to tell the story of <span>Chinese</span> characters and how to practice <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy. If you are interested in <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy, this is a great opportunity for you to learn the history and the beauty of <span>Chinese</span> characters. You are welcome to bring in your <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy tools to practice following the instruction from the video. Our website also has collected some beautiful <span>Chinese</span> calligraphy pictures from the web. You may view them at <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool,org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','This Saturday Event - Michigan Chinese School (10/3/09)',0,'','publish','closed','open','','this-saturday-event-michigan-chinese-school-10309','','','2010-01-22 01:45:01','2010-01-22 05:45:01','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=11',0,'post','',0),(12,1,'2010-01-22 01:46:08','2010-01-22 05:46:08','Dear MCS parents,\n\nWe held our first Parents Assembly last Saturday. About 40 parents attended this meeting. School staff presented school status and 2009-2010 budget. This semester we registered 24 new students and 84 old students. Our enrollment rate reversed the declining trend in the past few years and added 3 more students comparing to last fall. Thanks for your effort in introducing our school to your friends. This Saturday we will issue the recruiting award check at parents lounge (room 2423/2425).\n\nLast Saturday we found a cell phone at women\'s restroom opposite to room 2419. You may come to the Parent lounge this Saturday to claim it if you are the owner.\n\nWe will pass out moon cakes to every student this Saturday to celebrate <span>Chinese</span> Moon Festival. We will also show a video to tell the story of <span>Chinese</span> characters and how to practice <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy. If you are interested in <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy, this is a great opportunity for you to learn the history and the beauty of <span>Chinese</span> characters. You are welcome to bring in your <span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy tools to practice following the instruction from the video. Our website also has collected some beautiful <span>Chinese</span> calligraphy pictures from the web. You may view them at <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool,org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\n\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS','This Saturday Event - Michigan Chinese School (10/3/09)',0,'','inherit','open','open','','11-autosave','','','2010-01-22 01:46:08','2010-01-22 05:46:08','',11,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=12',0,'revision','',0),(13,1,'2010-01-22 01:48:57','2010-01-22 05:48:57','MCS parents,\r\n\r\nParents on duty list is posted on MCS website.\r\n<div>Here is the link address of MCS Parents\' On-Duty Schedule for 2009-2010  School Year</div>\r\n<div><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/temp/MCS-2009-2010-Calendar_Parents-On-Duty.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/temp/MCS-2009-2010-Calendar_Parents-On-Duty.html</a></div>\r\nPlease review and mark your calendar accordingly.\r\n王 漢林 &amp; 呂宗龍 are parents on duty this coming Saturday. You may want to check our website from time to time for new job openings, great articles, class activities..etc..\r\n\r\nWe have several new students joined our school in the past couple of weeks. We would like to extend our welcome to the new students and new parents. Up to now we have 111 students registered. Hopefully this is the sign that Michigan economy is recovering.\r\n\r\nWe are preparing our school directory and collecting advertisements from local business. On our directory, we ask for $100 for a full page advertisement and $60 for half page. The income will help to offset the school operation cost gaps. You may contact JauYeu Lai or me  if you know anyone who maybe interested in posting advertisement on MCS directory.\r\n\r\nThis coming Saturday at parents lounge we will have some <span>Chinese</span> dish for sale from Hunan-Hunan restaurant. Here\'s the message from 双湘园的陈太太: 星期六.十七号.我想去卖些小吃.咸酥鸡.糯米肠.牛肉馅饼.\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-size-adjust: inherit; font-stretch: inherit;\" valign=\"top\">鸡肉馅饼.夫妻肺片.台湾本土泡菜.牛肉卷饼.鲜虾韭黄水饺.那天我会给大家试吃品尝.希望大家喜欢.謝謝。Don\'t miss this opportunity.\r\n\r\nTo these parents who ordered <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">粽</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">子, </span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">粽</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">子</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">將於</span>10/17 <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">星期六</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\"> </span>1:30PM <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">送到家長休息室</span>\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody></table>','MCS School Updates - 10/17/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-school-updates-101709','','','2010-01-22 01:48:57','2010-01-22 05:48:57','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=13',0,'post','',0),(14,1,'2010-01-22 01:48:33','2010-01-22 05:48:33','','MCS School Updates - 10/17/09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','13-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:48:33','2010-01-22 05:48:33','',13,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=14',0,'revision','',0),(15,1,'2010-01-22 01:50:03','2010-01-22 05:50:03','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI was told recently that some students spent all recess time between classes playing video games. It\'s a distraction to their learning at school. We encourage all students to chat and play with friends during recess instead of playing video games. Please ask your kids not to bring video games to <span>Chinese</span> school.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday Hunan-Hunan restaurant will bring in \"Stinky ToFu\" and \"Stinky Pot\" for  our parents to taste and order. You may also call 313-389-0939 to order for delivery on Saturday.\r\n\r\nOur webmasters Jauyeu (<a href=\"mailto:Jauyeulai@yahoo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Jauyeulai@yahoo.com</a>) &amp; Steven (<a href=\"mailto:tengkolien@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">tengkolien@gmail.com</a>) are looking for new pictures for slide show on MCS website. Our current slide show subject is \"<span>Chinese</span> Calligraphy\". Our next slide show subject will be \"Taiwan Scenery by MCS parents\". If you have any pictures about Taiwan that you would like to share, you may send the files to JauYeu &amp; Steven by the end of the month. This is a great opportunity to share with our kids the beauty of Taiwan island.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS communication - 10/24/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-102409','','','2010-01-22 01:50:03','2010-01-22 05:50:03','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=15',0,'post','',0),(16,1,'2010-01-22 01:50:46','2010-01-22 05:50:46','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nThis Saturday 10/31 is Halloween. We will held a Halloween parade during the break starting around 2:30pm. Treats will be passed out by school staff. We encourage all students and parents to wear Halloween costume. Considering that we have very young kids in the school, please do not wear mask, toy weapons (knife, gun..etc) and any bloody stuff.\r\n\r\nMr. Jauyeu Lai will take pictures for this activity and post them on MCS website. This year we will have a Halloween costume contest. 12 students will be selected to compete in the following 3 categories. The winner in each category will get a $20 gift card award.\r\n\r\n1. Best Halloween costume\r\n2. Most creative costume design\r\n3. Most green costume design (utilize of recycle material, waste, ...)\r\n\r\nJesse Wei, Tracy Wu and TingWei Lwo will be our judges. They will start the judging event around 1:30pm. So, don\'t wait till the parade to dress up the costume. We will try to begin the award ceremony at end of the parade.\r\n\r\nStarting this Saturday is our <span>Chinese</span> reading month. Students are encouraged to read <span>Chinese</span> books, watch <span>Chinese</span> movies....   Students who complete 240 minutes reading will be given a $5 reward.  Your children\'s  classroom teachers have books to share with the students. Recording sheet is  attached.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you have any suggestions.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 10/31/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-103109','','','2010-01-22 01:50:46','2010-01-22 05:50:46','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=16',0,'post','',0),(17,1,'2010-01-22 01:50:26','2010-01-22 05:50:26','','MCS Communication - 10/31/09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','16-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:50:26','2010-01-22 05:50:26','',16,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=17',0,'revision','',0),(18,1,'2010-01-22 01:51:38','2010-01-22 05:51:38','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nWe had a wonderful Halloween parade and contest last week. I\'d like to congratulate the three winners: <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\r\n\r\nCeleste Lai</span> - 1st grade (Best Halloween Costume), <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\r\nJessica Wu</span> - Ma 11 (Most Green Costume Design), <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\r\nEric Wu</span> - Senior class (Most Creative Costume Design).\r\n\r\nEach winner received a $20 gift card. We also have 12 students selected into the final contest. Each of them received a $5 gift card and a goodie bag. I trust that most kids and parents had a great time in participating and taking pictures. If you have any good pictures that would like to share, please send the pictures to JauYeu (<a href=\"mailto:jauyeulai@yahoo.com\" target=\"_blank\">jauyeulai@yahoo.com</a>) &amp; Steven (<a href=\"mailto:tengkolien@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">tengkolien@gmail.com</a>). They will post them on MCS website. Jauyeu Lai has  already posted the pictures he took on our website: <a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\r\nYou may also find new class pictures in the \"class activity\" link and new job openings.\r\n\r\nWe sold $935 tickets for the Double-Tenth concert. Although MCS is not the biggest <span>Chinese</span> school among the local 4, we have sold most tickets comparing to other schools. <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">We were awarded $861 </span>from the Double-Tenth organization committe. Thanks for all parents participating this event!\r\n<div><strong>Reminder - Reading month starts</strong></div>\r\n<div>Students are encouraged to read <span>Chinese</span> books, watch <span>Chinese</span> movies....  Students who complete 240 minutes will be given $5 reward.  Your  children\'s classroom teachers have books to share with the students. Recording  sheets have been passed out last week.</div>\r\nThis week <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">方漢華 and Mike Freeman</span> are parents on duty. Please report to Wen Chang at 1:30pm.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">School directory is ready.</span> Don\'t forget to pick it up this Saturday at Parents room. Thanks for the effort from our MCS parents and staff, especially Jauyeu Lai, who put in a lot of efforts to compile the directory contents and collect Ads. The Ads income is not only able to cover the directory expense but also contribute a few hundred dollars to our school budget.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Hunan Hunan</span> will be at our school again this Saturday. There will be a new dish  available \"drunken chicken\". You may call to put in orders or if you  have any questions, before Friday 9:00, (313) 398-0939.\r\n\r\nThanks for your continuous support and together, we will make MCS a fun and exciting place for our kids to learn <span>Chinese</span>.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 11/7/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-11709','','','2010-01-22 01:51:38','2010-01-22 05:51:38','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=18',0,'post','',0),(19,1,'2010-01-22 01:51:19','2010-01-22 05:51:19','','MCS Communication - 11/7/09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','18-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:51:19','2010-01-22 05:51:19','',18,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=19',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2010-01-22 01:53:19','2010-01-22 05:53:19','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nLast school year our ex-principal Hou made an announcement to promote teaching and reciting 弟子規. Below is an extract from her e-mail on 3/9/2009:\r\n\r\n******************************\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-size-adjust: inherit; font-stretch: inherit;\" valign=\"top\">***********************************************************************\r\n<div>Dear parents:</div>\r\n<div>I am very happy to inform you that last Saturday, <span style=\"background-color: #ffff40;\">our school received a very generous donation  from a 王老先生.</span> His grand-daughter was once student in our school.  He is  donating his money to help promote the <span>Chinese</span> language and <span>Chinese</span> culture.  We  are <span>truly</span> grateful to his generosity.  In his honor, some teachers  in our school will start to add some old teachings from 弟子規 in their classes.</div>\r\n<div>I put together a PowerPoint presentation for 讀經班.  I presented it on  2/28 but not many parents showed up.  I think this will also be a good  opportunity for kids to learn some old teachings from our ancestor.  I intent to  make it a fun class with the goal of presenting the result in next year\'s New  Year Program.  If you are interested, please take a look at the attached  PowerPoint.  Students who can memorize the whole thing will be awarded $100.  Please let me know if you are interested in signing up your child/ren for this  class.\r\n*****************************************************************************************************\r\n\r\nEx-principal Hou made an attempt to assemble an extra-curriculum class for students to learn 弟子規. Attached file contains details of her proposal. Due to many reasons, the class couldn\'t attract enough students to become official. However, some students may have made an effort to recite the whole article and might be very disappointed if the $100 award is gone with the class. In our teachers meeting held last month, we decided to continue the commitment of offering $100 awrad to students who can recite the complete article 弟子規.\r\n\r\nStudents may come forward to recite the complete 弟子規 in front of our committe (教務主任, 校長) on 1/30/2010 at parents lounge after regular class. We will award $100 in the New Year Celebration Party (2/6/2010) to students who memorize the complete article and recite fluently. Students who intend to participate in this reciting event should notify their teacher before end of the fall semeter.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday Hunan-Hunan 双湘园 will come to school again with 滷味.雞棑便當.糯米大肠.粽子.醉雞.臭豆腐.肉圆.碗粿.\r\n\r\nParents on duty<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">: <span style=\"color: #0000ff; font-weight: bold;\">馮安強, 積博思</span></span>\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS</div></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody></table>','MCS Communication - 11/14/2009',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-11142009','','','2010-01-22 01:53:19','2010-01-22 05:53:19','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=20',0,'post','',0),(21,1,'2010-01-22 01:53:00','2010-01-22 05:53:00','','MCS Communication - 11/14/2009',0,'','inherit','open','open','','20-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:53:00','2010-01-22 05:53:00','',20,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=21',0,'revision','',0),(22,1,'2010-01-22 01:54:08','2010-01-22 05:54:08','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nEnjoy a quiet week before Thanksgiving!\r\n\r\nParents on duty this Saturday : <span style=\"font-weight: bold; color: #ff0000;\">蓋濟民, 王衛華</span>\r\n\r\nNew job opening for FEA analyst is posted on MCS website.\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 11/21/09',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-112109','','','2010-01-22 01:54:08','2010-01-22 05:54:08','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=22',0,'post','',0),(23,1,'2010-01-22 01:53:54','2010-01-22 05:53:54','','MCS Communication - 11/21/09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','22-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:53:54','2010-01-22 05:53:54','',22,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=23',0,'revision','',0),(24,1,'2010-01-22 01:54:44','2010-01-22 05:54:44','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI hope every student has enjoyed a wonderful Thanksgiving holiday and is ready for the coming <span>Chinese</span> school this Saturday. Don\'t forget that it\'s time to turn in the reading sheet for $5 reading award.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday we will have teaching staff meeting after school. Teachers need to attend. Parents are also welcome to participate for any suggestions.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">侯禹任,  許呈維</span>\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 12/5/2009',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-1252009','','','2010-01-22 01:54:44','2010-01-22 05:54:44','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=24',0,'post','',0),(25,1,'2010-01-22 01:54:29','2010-01-22 05:54:29','','MCS Communication - 12/5/2009',0,'','inherit','open','open','','24-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:54:29','2010-01-22 05:54:29','',24,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=25',0,'revision','',0),(26,1,'2010-01-22 01:55:29','2010-01-22 05:55:29','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\n12/12 is the last school day of the year. Since we won\'t be seeing you after this Saturday, I and our MCS staff wish everyone Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year! If you plan to have a trip during holidays, please place your family\'s safety in mind all the time while enjoying your get-away. In the past few years there were several ski accidents happened to our school\'s friends and families. So, have a fun and safe holidays!\r\n\r\nOur parents on duty this Saturday: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">周治太</span> &amp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">郭友信</span>\r\n\r\nThis Saturday we will start the selection of student hosts for 2/6/2010 <span>Chinese</span> New Year Celebration Party. Any students in 7th grades and above, are encouraged to participate. We will interview the students on 2:30pm at classroom 2401. The students will be interviewed with 2 questions:\r\n\r\n1. How do you introduce yourself to the public?\r\n2. Why you would like to be the host and what\'s your qualification?\r\n\r\nThis year we will have 6 students and 2 teachers to host our New Year Celebration. I believe our teachers have already informed some students to attend the selection. This is a good opportunity for student to learn public speech and on-stage performing.\r\n\r\nOur New Year Celebration will be held at Livonia Stevenson High School on 2/6/2010 Saturday. Program runs from 3pm to 5:30pm with performance from each class and parents. Parents who may be interested in performing may contact either Jim Yang or Patti Fu to be included in the program. Dinner starts at 6pm along with several games for students to play. This year, we decided to discount our dinner ticket to the following price to counteract the Michigan recession (or depression based on who you talked to):\r\n\r\nAdult ticket: $5, kids  under 12: $3, kids under 3: free (Tickets will be on sale early next year)\r\n\r\nOur PTA Chairman Jim Yang has worked out dinner menu and restaurant with class representatives. You may ask your class representative for details. We welcome you and your whole family to join to celebrate the <span>Chinese</span> Tiger year.\r\n\r\nAs in the past years, we welcome company sponsors for this New Year event. Please let me know if you or anyone you know that may donate funds or gifts for this event. A few years ago Ameriplus financial company helped to offload part of the school budget burden in this event. I sure hope we have the same luck this year.\r\n\r\nNote: Students completed the reading month requirements will be awarded this week in each class.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 12/12/2009',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-12122009','','','2010-01-22 01:55:29','2010-01-22 05:55:29','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=26',0,'post','',0),(27,1,'2010-01-22 01:55:12','2010-01-22 05:55:12','','MCS Communication - 12/12/2009',0,'','inherit','open','open','','26-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:55:12','2010-01-22 05:55:12','',26,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=27',0,'revision','',0),(28,1,'2010-01-22 01:56:13','2010-01-22 05:56:13','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nHappy 2010! I wish you all have enjoyed a very pleasant holiday and are ready for a fresh start of the new year.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday we have several things going:\r\n\r\n1. The Fall semester ends on 1/23 and Spring semester begins on 1/30. We will start student registration this Saturday. Don\'t forget to bring your check book to the school. Like in the Fall semester, we still offer $50 tuition rebate for every new student you recruit.\r\n\r\n2. We will start ticket sale for 2/6 New Year celebration dinner. To encourage your participation along with consideration of current depressed economy, the ticket price is discounted to $5 for adult and $3 for kids under 12. PTA chair Jim Yang has selected a <span>Chinese</span> restaurant famous for traditional Taiwanese food to host the buffet. Dinner menu was decided by all class representatives. Please contact them for details.\r\n\r\n3. This year we will have both adults and students to host the New Year Celebration. The following students were interviewed and selected as student hosts: Irene Li, Jessica Wu, Justin Hsieh, Eric Tang, Timothy Lu and Eric Li. These students should meet with teachers Patty Fu and WeiLi Yang after regular class to start practice.\r\n\r\n4. During New Year Celebration we will award scholarship to students ranked top 25% in the class (the rule was published in previous MCS communication). Please encourage your kids to work hard in the next 3 weeks to improve his or her grades (listed in the student record sheet that most teachers provided to you from time to time).\r\n\r\n5. Parents on duty: 呂思平, 藍任昇\r\n\r\n6. Hunan-Hunan will deliver your <span>Chinese</span> food orders to parents room every 2nd and 4th week. So, your may pick up your food orders this Saturday.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you have any questions or  comments.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 1/9/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-192010','','','2010-01-22 01:56:13','2010-01-22 05:56:13','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=28',0,'post','',0),(29,1,'2010-01-22 01:55:56','2010-01-22 05:55:56','','MCS Communication - 1/9/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','28-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:55:56','2010-01-22 05:55:56','',28,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=29',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2010-01-22 01:56:44','2010-01-22 05:56:44','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nReminders:\r\n\r\n1. The Fall semester ends on 1/23 and Spring semester begins on 1/30. We will continue student registration this Saturday. Don\'t forget to bring your check book to the school. Like in the Fall semester, we still offer $50 tuition rebate for every new student you recruit.\r\n\r\n2. We have startedticket sale for 2/6 New  Year celebration dinner. To encourage your participation along with  consideration of current depressed economy, the ticket price is discounted to $5  for adult and $3 for students (corrected from previous communication). PTA chair Jim Yang has selected a <span>Chinese</span> restaurant famous for traditional Taiwanese food to host the buffet. Dinner menu is attached.\r\n\r\n3. Student hosts: Irene Li, Jessica Wu, Justin Hsieh, Eric Tang, Timothy Lu and  Eric Li. should meet with teachers Patty Fu after  regular class to start practice.\r\n\r\n4. During New Year Celebration we will  award scholarship to students ranked top 25% in the class (the rule was  published in previous MCS communication). Please encourage your kids to work  hard in the next 2 weeks to improve his or her grades (listed in the student  record sheet that most teachers provided to you from time to time).\r\n\r\n5. As stated in 11/14 MCS communication, students who would like to recite the complete 弟子規 should inform the teacher and present it on 1/30. I\'d like to see some students be able to receive the $100 award.\r\n\r\n6. Parents on duty: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">洗孝輝, 葉士銘</span>\r\n\r\nOur Lego Robotics extra-curriculum class will assemble three teams (one 8th grade team, one 7th grade team, one 5-6th grade team) to attend 2010 Robofest competition at Canton Charter Academy on March 27. They did really well last year. I appreciate instructors MengFeng Li and Wen Chang for their consistent dedication to the class. Wish the best for our Roboteams! GO! GO!\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 1/16/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-1162010','','','2010-01-22 01:56:44','2010-01-22 05:56:44','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=30',0,'post','',0),(31,1,'2010-01-22 01:57:25','2010-01-22 05:57:25','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nThere are two new updates posted on MCS website (<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>) that you maybe interested:\r\n\r\n1. 2010 全美中華歷史文化常識比賽\r\n2. Concert of Taiwanese Music at Farmington Community Library, Feb. 7, 2:30pm\r\n\r\nReminder:\r\n\r\n1. Spring semester registration is still on going.\r\n2. <span>Chinese</span> New Year Dinner ticket sale.\r\n3. Parents on duty: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">王棋洲, 黃皓雯</span>\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will deliver <span>Chinese</span> food you ordered to the school this Saturday.\r\n\r\nTo these parents who ordered <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">粽</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">子, </span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">粽</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">子will be delivered this Saturday to the 1st floor lounge near <span>Chinese</span> school entrance.</span>\r\n\r\n僑 務委員會 offered some free 2010 calendars to our school. These calendars feature beautiful Taiwan flowers. We will pass it out at Parents Lounge this Saturday.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 1/23/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-1232010','','','2010-01-22 01:57:25','2010-01-22 05:57:25','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=31',0,'post','',0),(32,1,'2010-01-22 01:57:09','2010-01-22 05:57:09','','MCS Communication - 1/23/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','31-revision','','','2010-01-22 01:57:09','2010-01-22 05:57:09','',31,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=32',0,'revision','',0),(33,1,'2010-01-22 01:58:32','2010-01-22 05:58:32','Dear MCS parents,\n\nThere are two new updates posted on MCS website (<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>) that you maybe interested:\n\n1. 2010 全美中華歷史文化常識比賽\n2. Concert of Taiwanese Music at Farmington Community Library, Feb. 7, 2:30pm\n\nReminder:\n\n1. Spring semester registration is still on going.\n2. <span>Chinese</span> New Year Dinner ticket sale.\n3. Parents on duty: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">王棋洲, 黃皓雯</span>\n\nHunan-Hunan will deliver <span>Chinese</span> food you ordered to the school this Saturday.\n\nTo these parents who ordered <span lang=\"ZH-CN\">粽</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">子, </span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">粽</span><span lang=\"ZH-CN\">子will be delivered this Saturday to the 1st floor lounge near <span>Chinese</span> school entrance.</span>\n\n僑 務委員會 offered some free 2010 calendars to our school. These calendars feature beautiful Taiwan flowers. We will pass it out at Parents Lounge this Saturday.\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 1/23/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','31-autosave','','','2010-01-22 01:58:32','2010-01-22 05:58:32','',31,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=33',0,'revision','',0),(34,1,'2010-01-29 00:19:36','2010-01-29 04:19:36','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nThis Saturday is the first day of school for spring semester. I believe you may have received student reports of last semester from the teachers already. For students with excellent academic achievements last semester (top 25% of the class), we will award $20 scholarship in the New Year Celebration.\r\n\r\nFor students in 7th grade and above, we encourage you to participate in the Chinese SAT II mockup test. Please bring in your registration form and $10 registration fee. We will send out MCS group registration by 2/2. Attached is the SAT II registration form.\r\n\r\nThe following Saturday 2/6 is our New Year Celebration. You may still purchase dinner tickets this Saturday.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 黃正寧, 陸樹德\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal,  MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/ </a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/密西根中文學校-SAT-Test.doc\">密西根中文學校 SAT Test</a></a>','MCS Communication - 1/30/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-1302010','','','2010-01-29 00:19:37','2010-01-29 04:19:37','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=34',0,'post','',0),(35,1,'2010-01-29 00:18:54','2010-01-29 04:18:54','','密西根中文學校 SAT Test',0,'','inherit','open','open','','%e5%af%86%e8%a5%bf%e6%a0%b9%e4%b8%ad%e6%96%87%e5%ad%b8%e6%a0%a1-sat-test','','','2010-01-29 00:18:54','2010-01-29 04:18:54','',34,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/密西根中文學校-SAT-Test.doc',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(36,1,'2010-01-29 00:16:50','2010-01-29 04:16:50','Dear MCS parents,\n\nThis Saturday is the first day of school for spring semester. I believe you may have received student reports of last semester from the teachers already. For students with excellent academic achievements last semester (top 25% of the class), we will award $20 scholarship in the New Year Celebration.\n\nFor students in 7th grade and above, we encourage you to participate in the Chinese SAT II mockup test. Please bring in your registration form and $10 registration fee. We will send out MCS group registration by 2/2. Attached is the SAT II registration form.\n\nThe following Saturday 2/6 is our New Year Celebration. You may still purchase dinner tickets this Saturday.\n\nParents on duty: 黃正寧, 陸樹德\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal,  MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/ </a>','MCS Communication - 1/30/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','34-revision','','','2010-01-29 00:16:50','2010-01-29 04:16:50','',34,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=36',0,'revision','',0),(37,1,'2010-02-04 23:51:15','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<div>Dear MCS parents,</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>Happy Chinese New Year and no school for this Saturday and next Saturday!</div>\n<div>Our New Year Celebration Party starts on 3PM at Stevenson High School followed with dinner party at 6PM. Program schedule has been posted on MCS website for your review. You may also find pictures taken from last year\'s New Year Party in the school Album under directory \"sly\". Since the New Year Party is organized and prepared by all of us, students, parents and school staff, I believe we will have great fun together to celebrate the start of Chinese Tiger Year.</div>\n<div>Regarding to the recitation of \"弟子規\", one student recited 95% of the book last week. He may finish the complete book if there are more time for prepration. Several students also expressed interest to recite the complete book if there are more time allowed for preparation. Therefore, to encourage more student participation, we will extend the deadline till end of May. Students who may recite the complete \"弟子規\" at the end of May will be awarded $100 at the school Graduation Ceremony in June.</div>\n<div>Spring semester registration has ended. We have 3 new students and lost 6 students for various reasons. Total student count is 108 for this semester. Please offer your welcome to the new faces when you meet them in the school or in the New Year Party.</div>\n<div>Have a great weekend!</div>\n<div>Best Regards</div>\n<div>Alex Tang</div>\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/6/2010',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2010-02-04 23:51:15','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=37',0,'post','',0),(38,1,'2010-02-04 23:52:14','2010-02-05 03:52:14','Dear MCS parents,\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nHappy Chinese New Year and no school for this Saturday and next Saturday!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nOur New Year Celebration Party starts on 3PM at Stevenson High School followed with dinner party at 6PM. Program schedule has been posted on MCS website for your review. You may also find pictures taken from last year\'s New Year Party in the school Album under directory \"sly\". Since the New Year Party is organized and prepared by all of us, students, parents and school staff, I believe we will have great fun together to celebrate the start of Chinese Tiger Year.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nRegarding to the recitation of \"弟子規\", one student recited 95% of the book last week. He may finish the complete book if there are more time for prepration. Several students also expressed interest to recite the complete book if there are more time allowed for preparation. Therefore, to encourage more student participation, we will extend the deadline till end of May. Students who may recite the complete \"弟子規\" at the end of May will be awarded $100 at the school Graduation Ceremony in June.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nSpring semester registration has ended. We have 3 new students and lost 6 students for various reasons. Total student count is 108 for this semester. Please offer your welcome to the new faces when you meet them in the school or in the New Year Party.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nHave a great weekend!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAlex Tang\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/6/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-262010','','','2010-02-04 23:52:14','2010-02-05 03:52:14','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=38',0,'post','',0),(39,1,'2010-02-04 23:51:36','2010-02-05 03:51:36','<h1>MCS Communication - 2/6/2010</h1>','MCS Communication - 2/6/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','38-revision','','','2010-02-04 23:51:36','2010-02-05 03:51:36','',38,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=39',0,'revision','',0),(40,1,'2010-02-04 23:53:26','2010-02-05 03:53:26','Dear MCS parents,\n<div>\n\nHappy Chinese New Year and no school for this Saturday and next Saturday!\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nOur New Year Celebration Party starts on 3PM at Stevenson High School followed with dinner party at 6PM. Program schedule has been posted on MCS website for your review. You may also find pictures taken from last year\'s New Year Party in the school Album under directory \"sly\". Since the New Year Party is organized and prepared by all of us, students, parents and school staff, I believe we will have great fun together to celebrate the start of Chinese Tiger Year.\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nRegarding to the recitation of \"弟子規\", one student recited 95% of the book last week. He may finish the complete book if there are more time for prepration. Several students also expressed interest to recite the complete book if there are more time allowed for preparation. Therefore, to encourage more student participation, we will extend the deadline till end of May. Students who may recite the complete \"弟子規\" at the end of May will be awarded $100 at the school Graduation Ceremony in June.\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nSpring semester registration has ended. We have 3 new students and lost 6 students for various reasons. Total student count is 108 for this semester. Please offer your welcome to the new faces when you meet them in the school or in the New Year Party.\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nHave a great weekend!\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nBest Regards\n\n</div>\n<div>\n\nAlex Tang\n\n</div>\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/6/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','38-autosave','','','2010-02-04 23:53:26','2010-02-05 03:53:26','',38,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=40',0,'revision','',0),(41,1,'2010-02-19 00:55:12','2010-02-19 04:55:12','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nHappy Chinese New Year!\r\n\r\nI wish everyone has enjoyed our New Year Party and a quiet mid-winter break weekend. Thanks for your participation! I heard a lot of compliments on this year\'s dinner food. Please give a loud applause to our PTA chair - Jim Yang. He not only coordinated the preparation work of this event, but also contributed his professional singing performance during the party. If you are interested to be the next white-horse-prince, you may sign up for his extra-curriculum guitar class this weekend.\r\n\r\nWe also want to thank the two students that performed the talk show:  鄺紹耘 &amp; 王淨德. and our six student hosts: 李藹玲,李祥, 唐涵中, 謝耀廷,吳品萱,呂詠恩. This Year 蔡耀霆 volunteered to paint the big tiger for our stage decoration again. He painted a big Mouse for MCS 2008 New Year Party decoration. Due to time conflict, he won\'t be attending MCS this semester. Thank you 耀霆 and wish you the best for your future!\r\n\r\nOur two beautiful hosts: Patty Fu and WeiLi Yang devoted a lot effort and time to make  the Party full of fun. I can\'t say enough to express my appreciation. This Saturday we will start selling the New Year Party DVD recorded by JauYeu Lai for $5 a set. You may own a long lasting memory of your kids and performance of our beautiful hosts. So don\'t forget to bring your cash for it.\r\n\r\nWe need more kids to participate in the extra-curriculum class and activity. The  following classes are still open for enrollment:\r\n1. Lion dance team - learn to be part of Chinese culture with a group of young &amp; energetic Chinese students.\r\n2. English writing for SAT - still need a couple more students that may want to sharpen the English writing skills\r\n3. Guitar class -  Want to impress your friends with the guitar music? Our PTA chair Jim Yang who used to perform guitar and singing back in Taiwan will guide you step by step towards your dream\r\n\r\nOK, our parents on duty this week are: 馬國驥,               江政承\r\n\r\nDon\'t forget to visit our web site from time to time for new learning &amp; job opportunity.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/20/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-2202010','','','2010-02-19 00:55:12','2010-02-19 04:55:12','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=41',0,'post','',0),(42,1,'2010-02-19 00:55:07','2010-02-19 04:55:07','Dear MCS parents,\n\nHappy Chinese New Year!\n\nI wish everyone has enjoyed our New Year Party and a quiet mid-winter break weekend. Thanks for your participation! I heard a lot of compliments on this year\'s dinner food. Please give a loud applause to our PTA chair - Jim Yang. He not only coordinated the preparation work of this event, but also contributed his professional singing performance during the party. If you are interested to be the next white-horse-prince, you may sign up for his extra-curriculum guitar class this weekend.\n\nWe also want to thank the two students that performed the talk show:  鄺紹耘 &amp; 王淨德. and our six student hosts: 李藹玲,李祥, 唐涵中, 謝耀廷,吳品萱,呂詠恩. This Year 蔡耀霆 volunteered to paint the big tiger for our stage decoration again. He painted a big Mouse for MCS 2008 New Year Party decoration. Due to time conflict, he won\'t be attending MCS this semester. Thank you 耀霆 and wish you the best for your future!\n\nOur two beautiful hosts: Patty Fu and WeiLi Yang devoted a lot effort and time to make  the Party full of fun. I can\'t say enough to express my appreciation. This Saturday we will start selling the New Year Party DVD recorded by JauYeu Lai for $5 a set. You may own a long lasting memory of your kids and performance of our beautiful hosts. So don\'t forget to bring your cash for it.\n\nWe need more kids to participate in the extra-curriculum class and activity. The  following classes are still open for enrollment:\n1. Lion dance team - learn to be part of Chinese culture with a group of young &amp; energetic Chinese students.\n2. English writing for SAT - still need a couple more students that may want to sharpen the English writing skills\n3. Guitar class -  Want to impress your friends with the guitar music? Our PTA chair Jim Yang who used to perform guitar and singing back in Taiwan will guide you step by step towards your dream\n\nOK, our parents on duty this week are: 馬國驥,               江政承\n\nDon\'t forget to visit our web site from time to time for new learning &amp; job opportunity.\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 2/20/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','41-revision','','','2010-02-19 00:55:07','2010-02-19 04:55:07','',41,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=42',0,'revision','',0),(43,1,'2010-02-27 01:41:47','2010-02-27 05:41:47','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nAs shown in the following extracts from our PTA chair Jim Yang\'s e-mail:\r\n+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\r\n各位家長代表,\r\n\r\n本人因工作關係將於三月初回台, 考量到接下來家長會長的工作任務無法續任,\r\n所以決定將於本周六2/27 ,1:40 pm 召開臨時家長大會介紹新任家長會長劉怡均小姐(Julia),同時她也將接任一年級班家長代表的工作.\r\n本人在此特別感謝劉小姐的幫忙 ,也懇請各位代表能夠多多支持她, 再次感謝各位-\r\n+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\r\n\r\nJim will pursue a new career in Taiwan starting next month. Even though his term in MCS was short, Jim\'s contribution to MCS is well recognized and visible. For instance, as we put it on the New Year Party DVD, his decoration at central stage, his guitar and singing performance, his arrangements on the dinner menu, plus all behind the scene coordinations. Thanks Jim and we all wish you to become a millionaire entrepreneur soon.\r\n\r\nWe also want to thank Julia Liu 劉怡均小姐 for her willingness to fill in Jim\'s position. Julia has been actively assisting 1st grade teacher in the classroom. I believe her passion to make MCS a better place for our kids will sure earn everyone\'s support. Please offer her your support when you meet her on the hallway this Saturday.\r\n\r\nReminders of the week:\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n--- Teachers will present $10 \"Perfect Attendance Award\" in the class. There are 47 students earned this award in the fall semester. Please congratulate your kids on this award and I wish more kids may earn it this semester.\r\n--- Hunan-Hunan (313-389-0939) will deliver your Chinese food orders this week\r\n--- Yang Sui-Juan (313-717-3382) will deliver your Chinese snack orders this week\r\n--- More new updates on MCS website (pictures, jobs, articles..)\r\n--- New Year Party DVD will be delivered, you may also order it this Saturday\r\n--- Parents on duty: 鄺力衡, 連登科\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 2/27/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-2272010','','','2010-02-27 01:41:47','2010-02-27 05:41:47','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=43',0,'post','',0),(44,1,'2010-02-27 01:41:40','2010-02-27 05:41:40','Dear MCS parents,\n\nAs shown in the following extracts from our PTA chair Jim Yang\'s e-mail:\n+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n各位家長代表,\n\n本人因工作關係將於三月初回台, 考量到接下來家長會長的工作任務無法續任,\n所以決定將於本周六2/27 ,1:40 pm 召開臨時家長大會介紹新任家長會長劉怡均小姐(Julia),同時她也將接任一年級班家長代表的工作.\n本人在此特別感謝劉小姐的幫忙 ,也懇請各位代表能夠多多支持她, 再次感謝各位-\n+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n\nJim will pursue a new career in Taiwan starting next month. Even though his term in MCS was short, Jim\'s contribution to MCS is well recognized and visible. For instance, as we put it on the New Year Party DVD, his decoration at central stage, his guitar and singing performance, his arrangements on the dinner menu, plus all behind the scene coordinations. Thanks Jim and we all wish you to become a millionaire entrepreneur soon.\n\nWe also want to thank Julia Liu 劉怡均小姐 for her willingness to fill in Jim\'s position. Julia has been actively assisting 1st grade teacher in the classroom. I believe her passion to make MCS a better place for our kids will sure earn everyone\'s support. Please offer her your support when you meet her on the hallway this Saturday.\n\nReminders of the week:\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n--- Teachers will present $10 \"Perfect Attendance Award\" in the class. There are 47 students earned this award in the fall semester. Please congratulate your kids on this award and I wish more kids may earn it this semester.\n--- Hunan-Hunan (313-389-0939) will deliver your Chinese food orders this week\n--- Yang Sui-Juan (313-717-3382) will deliver your Chinese snack orders this week\n--- More new updates on MCS website (pictures, jobs, articles..)\n--- New Year Party DVD will be delivered, you may also order it this Saturday\n--- Parents on duty: 鄺力衡, 連登科\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 2/27/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','43-revision','','','2010-02-27 01:41:40','2010-02-27 05:41:40','',43,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=44',0,'revision','',0),(45,1,'2010-02-27 01:42:53','2010-02-27 05:42:53','Dear MCS parents,\n\nAs shown in the following extracts from our PTA chair Jim Yang\'s e-mail:\n+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n各位家長代表,\n\n本人因工作關係將於三月初回台, 考量到接下來家長會長的工作任務無法續任,\n所以決定將於本周六2/27 ,1:40 pm 召開臨時家長大會介紹新任家長會長劉怡均小姐(Julia),同時她也將接任一年級班家長代表的工作.\n本人在此特別感謝劉小姐的幫忙 ,也懇請各位代表能夠多多支持她, 再次感謝各位-\n+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n\nJim will pursue a new career in Taiwan starting next month. Even though his term in MCS was short, Jim\'s contribution to MCS is well recognized and visible. For instance, as we put it on the New Year Party DVD, his decoration at central stage, his guitar and singing performance, his arrangements on the dinner menu, plus all behind the scene coordinations. Thanks Jim and we all wish you to become a millionaire entrepreneur soon.\n\nWe also want to thank Julia Liu 劉怡均小姐 for her willingness to fill in Jim\'s position. Julia has been actively assisting 1st grade teacher in the classroom. I believe her passion to make MCS a better place for our kids will sure earn everyone\'s support. Please offer her your support when you meet her on the hallway this Saturday.\n\nReminders of the week:\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n--- Teachers will present $10 \"Perfect Attendance Award\" in the class. There are 47 students earned this award in the fall semester. Please congratulate your kids on this award and I wish more kids may earn it this semester.\n--- Hunan-Hunan (313-389-0939) will deliver your Chinese food orders this week\n--- Yang Sui-Juan (313-717-3382) will deliver your Chinese snack orders this week\n--- More new updates on MCS website (pictures, jobs, articles..)\n--- New Year Party DVD will be delivered, you may also order it this Saturday\n--- Parents on duty: 鄺力衡, 連登科\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 2/27/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','43-autosave','','','2010-02-27 01:42:53','2010-02-27 05:42:53','',43,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=45',0,'revision','',0),(46,1,'2010-03-05 00:57:39','2010-03-05 04:57:39','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI\'d like to thank one of MCS parents 劉玪花 who donated 12 Chinese DVDs to the school last week. The DVDs are titled 坷拉傳奇. These videos are made by Taiwan Public TV as a series of puppet stories. Our teachers may chose to show part of it in the next few weeks.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday I have invited Mrs. Pallas Wang to come to our school to share her thoughts on promoting \"弟子規\". On behalf of her father-in-law Mr. Wang, she donated $2000 to MCS last year. It\'s pretty sad that Mr. Wang passed away a couple weeks ago. Pallas decided to donate the money her family received from the funeral to MCS. She also plans to sponsor the award for students who may recite the complete \"弟子規\". Please come to the parents lounge during class hour to learn from Pallas more about the promotion campaign  for learning \"弟子規\".\r\n\r\nWe will also pass out the New Year Party DVDs. I am really amazed by the way the videos are edited. JauYeu Lai did an outstanding job and please, let\'s all give him a huge applause.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 舒志翔, 李青\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 3/6/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-362010','','','2010-03-05 00:57:39','2010-03-05 04:57:39','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=46',0,'post','',0),(47,1,'2010-03-12 23:04:09','2010-03-13 03:04:09','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nLast week Mrs. Pallas Wang 杜愛白 女士 donated $970 to our school to support scholarship system we instituted this year. She also decided to sponsor scholarship to students who may recite 弟子規. According to her suggestion, the awarding policy has been changed to the following:\r\n\r\nThere are 6 sections in 弟子規. Students may get $10 award for each section he or she recited. Students who may recite the complete 弟子規 will be awarded $100. Recitation may begin on the week of 5/15. Scholarship will be awarded during the school graduation ceremony.\r\n\r\nHere\'s the link to an ROC government website that has very helpful teaching material of 弟子規: <a href=\"http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/\" target=\"_blank\">http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/</a>\r\n\r\nThis week we will have Chinese SAT II mock up test. Please remind your kids who have registered for the test come to school on time with their own 2B pencil and eraser on Saturday.  The test will be held at 1:30PM in Room 2401. Students who are in either Ma-Li-Ping classes or senior class and not taking the test, should take the 7th grade class instead.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 王鴻烈 &amp;                王武駒\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will deliver your Chinese food orders this Saturday.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 3/13/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-3132010','','','2010-03-12 23:04:09','2010-03-13 03:04:09','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=47',0,'post','',0),(48,1,'2010-03-12 23:03:43','2010-03-13 03:03:43','Dear MCS parents,\n\nLast week Mrs. Pallas Wang 杜愛白 女士 donated $970 to our school to support scholarship system we instituted this year. She also decided to sponsor scholarship to students who may recite 弟子規. According to her suggestion, the awarding policy has been changed to the following:\n\nThere are 6 sections in 弟子規. Students may get $10 award for each section he or she recited. Students who may recite the complete 弟子規 will be awarded $100. Recitation may begin on the week of 5/15. Scholarship will be awarded during the school graduation ceremony.\n\nHere\'s the link to an ROC government website that has very helpful teaching material of 弟子規: <a href=\"http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/\" target=\"_blank\">http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/</a>\n\nThis week we will have Chinese SAT II mock up test. Please remind your kids who have registered for the test come to school on time with their own 2B pencil and eraser on Saturday.  The test will be held at 1:30PM in Room 2401. Students who are in either Ma-Li-Ping classes or senior class and not taking the test, should take the 7th grade class instead.\n\nParents on duty: 王鴻烈 &amp;                王武駒\n\nHunan-Hunan will deliver your Chinese food orders this Saturday.\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 3/13/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','47-revision','','','2010-03-12 23:03:43','2010-03-13 03:03:43','',47,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=48',0,'revision','',0),(49,1,'2010-03-18 23:59:23','2010-03-19 03:59:23','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI\'m glad to announce that Lisa Hou, MCS 2009 principal, will offer a seminar to you this week. She will cover investment vehicles that are available to the parents for setting up education funds, such as MET, UGMA, 529, MESP, etc. Please come to the Parents Lounge to enjoy Lisa\'s sharing of her knowledge and experience on these subject. The seminar will begin around 1:40pm and last for about an hour.\r\n\r\nThere was an incident happened in one classroom last week. The plastic cover of a ceiling light somehow fell to the floor. It\'s fortunate that no one got hurt. The incident was reported to the Madonna Univ. immediately. I\'m not sure whether the Univ. has examined all ceiling lights or not. However, please just take a cautious step in the classroom and report to us should you find any loosening ceiling light cover.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 余宏鴻, 陳德修\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication 3/20/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-3202010','','','2010-03-18 23:59:23','2010-03-19 03:59:23','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=49',0,'post','',0),(50,1,'2010-03-18 23:59:07','2010-03-19 03:59:07','','MCS Communication 3/20/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','49-revision','','','2010-03-18 23:59:07','2010-03-19 03:59:07','',49,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=50',0,'revision','',0),(51,1,'2010-04-03 23:21:19','2010-04-04 03:21:19','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nReminder: No school this weekend! Enjoy a spring break week but don\'t forget to prepare for the school speech contest on 4/17. Next school day - 4/10/2010.\r\n\r\nAttached please find information about a Chinese culture learning camp for this summer.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/招生簡章1.docx\">招生簡章</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/2010-Camp-English1.docx\">2010 Camp-English</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Registration-Form.xlsx\">Registration Form</a>','MCS Communication - 4/3/2010 - No School & 2010 Summer Camp Info',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-432010-no-school-2010-summer-camp-info','','','2010-04-03 23:21:19','2010-04-04 03:21:19','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=51',0,'post','',0),(52,1,'2010-04-03 23:18:22','2010-04-04 03:18:22','','招生簡章',0,'','inherit','open','open','','%e6%8b%9b%e7%94%9f%e7%b0%a1%e7%ab%a0','','','2010-04-03 23:18:22','2010-04-04 03:18:22','',51,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/招生簡章.docx',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(53,1,'2010-04-03 23:19:05','2010-04-04 03:19:05','','招生簡章',0,'','inherit','open','open','','%e6%8b%9b%e7%94%9f%e7%b0%a1%e7%ab%a0-2','','','2010-04-03 23:19:05','2010-04-04 03:19:05','',51,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/招生簡章1.docx',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(54,1,'2010-04-03 23:19:13','2010-04-04 03:19:13','','2010 Camp-English',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2010-camp-english','','','2010-04-03 23:19:13','2010-04-04 03:19:13','',51,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/2010-Camp-English.docx',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(55,1,'2010-04-03 23:19:18','2010-04-04 03:19:18','','Registration Form',0,'','inherit','open','open','','registration-form','','','2010-04-03 23:19:18','2010-04-04 03:19:18','',51,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Registration-Form.xlsx',0,'attachment','application/vnd.ms-excel',0),(56,1,'2010-04-03 23:19:53','2010-04-04 03:19:53','','2010 Camp-English',0,'','inherit','open','open','','2010-camp-english-2','','','2010-04-03 23:19:53','2010-04-04 03:19:53','',51,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/2010-Camp-English1.docx',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(57,1,'2010-04-03 23:17:22','2010-04-04 03:17:22','Dear MCS parents,\n\nReminder: No school this weekend! Enjoy a spring break week but don\'t forget to prepare for the school speech contest on 4/17. Next school day - 4/10/2010.\n\nAttached please find information about a Chinese culture learning camp for this summer.\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 4/3/2010 - No School & 2010 Summer Camp Info',0,'','inherit','open','open','','51-revision','','','2010-04-03 23:17:22','2010-04-04 03:17:22','',51,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=57',0,'revision','',0),(58,1,'2010-04-16 23:00:34','2010-04-17 03:00:34','<div>Dear MCS parents,</div>\r\n<div>This week we will have speech contest during the regular class hour and therefore class is cancelled. I hope every student is ready to perform their best in the contest.</div>\r\n<div>We are starting the process to nominate vice principal candidate for 2010-2011 school year. Please contact either me or Jessi or Julia if you or your friends are interested in leading MCS to create a better learning environment for our next generation.</div>\r\n<div>The following are some Chinese community information you maybe interested:</div>\r\n<div>1. Eric Wu, who used to be a MCS student, is offering a free after school tennis class to MCS students. Attached please find a flyer he passed out. I really appreciate his devotion to serve MCS with his talent. Please contact me if you are interested in attending this tennis training class (limited openings).</div>\r\n<div>2. There are scholarship opportunities offered by <span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">ASIAN AMERICAN GOVERNMENT EXECUTIVES NETWORK. Application deadline is 4/30. Please see the attachment for details.</span> </span></span></div>\r\n<div>3. The Council of Asian and Pacific Americans in Michign is sponsoring an Asian Cultural Dance Performance Show \"Splendor of the East\" on Friday, May 14, 2010 at 7 p.m. at Ford Community\r\nand Performing Arts Center in Dearborn. The organizer is looking for 2-3 volunteers from Chinese organization for the following work on May14:</div>\r\n<div>* food set up for the VIP reception</div>\r\n<div>* usher guests into the auditorium</div>\r\n<div>* runners for program participants</div>\r\n<div>* Others</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span>There will be discount in admission </span><span>( or possible free admission) for volunteers. </span>This is a good opoortunity to let youngsters to participate in this international cultural event. Please contact \"Sue Sung\" [<a href=\"mailto:sue.sung@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">sue.sung@gmail.com</a>] if you are interested. The poster is too big to send, you may find more details from the website <a title=\"http://capa-mi.org/\" href=\"http://capa-mi.org/\" target=\"_blank\">capa-mi.org</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>4.  Big Coming Event that I encourage all families to participate:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n\r\n<strong>*</strong><strong>Taiwanese American Heritage Week Cultural Fair*</strong>\r\n<strong>\r\nFriday</strong>, May 7th, 6:30-8pm @ Duderstadt Center Connector, The University of Michigan North Campus, 2281 Bonisteel Boulevard, Ann Arbor\r\n<strong>Saturday</strong>, May 8th, 10am-3pm @ Sheraton Hotel, 21111 Haggerty Road, Novi.\r\n\r\nIn celebration of Taiwanese American Heritage Week, all are invited to join the unique opportunity to see cultural presentations by renowned Taiwanese folk artisans in:\r\n* Lion Head (used in Lion Dance) Painting\r\n* Hand Puppetry\r\n* Dough Figuring Sculpture\r\n* Sugar Sculpture\r\n* Gourd Carving\r\n* Paper Umbrella Painting\r\n* Sculpture using tree bark, leaves, and other natural materials..\r\n* Silhouette paper cutting\r\nHands-on activities available for children and adults.   For details and  directions, please visit <a title=\"http://www.mitai.org\" href=\"http://www.mitai.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.mitai.org</a>.\r\n\r\nFREE. Donations welcome to help cover the material fees.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\r\n\r\nHave a great week!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Best Regards</div>\r\n<div>Alex Tang</div>\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/final_with_three_essays_and_one_time_change1.doc\">final_with_three_essays_and_one_time_change[1]</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/tennis.doc\">tennis</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Novi-poster1.jpg\">Novi poster.jpg</a>','MCS Communication - 4/17/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-4172010','','','2010-04-16 23:00:34','2010-04-17 03:00:34','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=58',0,'post','',0),(59,1,'2010-04-16 22:50:47','2010-04-17 02:50:47','','Novi poster',0,'','inherit','open','open','','novi-poster','','','2010-04-16 22:50:47','2010-04-17 02:50:47','',58,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Novi-poster.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(60,1,'2010-04-16 22:51:44','2010-04-17 02:51:44','','Novi poster',0,'','inherit','open','open','','novi-poster-2','','','2010-04-16 22:51:44','2010-04-17 02:51:44','',58,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/Novi-poster1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(61,1,'2010-04-16 22:53:48','2010-04-17 02:53:48','','tennis',0,'','inherit','open','open','','tennis','','','2010-04-16 22:53:48','2010-04-17 02:53:48','',58,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/tennis.doc',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(62,1,'2010-04-16 22:54:05','2010-04-17 02:54:05','','final_with_three_essays_and_one_time_change[1]',0,'','inherit','open','open','','final_with_three_essays_and_one_time_change1','','','2010-04-16 22:54:05','2010-04-17 02:54:05','',58,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/final_with_three_essays_and_one_time_change1.doc',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(63,1,'2010-04-16 22:49:22','2010-04-17 02:49:22','<div>Dear MCS parents,</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>This week we will have speech contest during the regular class hour and therefore class is cancelled. I hope every student is ready to perform their best in the contest.</div>\n<div>We are starting the process to nominate vice principal candidate for 2010-2011 school year. Please contact either me or Jessi or Julia if you or your friends are interested in leading MCS to create a better learning environment for our next generation.</div>\n<div>The following are some Chinese community information you maybe interested:</div>\n<div>1. Eric Wu, who used to be a MCS student, is offering a free after school tennis class to MCS students. Attached please find a flyer he passed out. I really appreciate his devotion to serve MCS with his talent. Please contact me if you are interested in attending this tennis training class (limited openings).</div>\n<div>2. There are scholarship opportunities offered by <span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">ASIAN AMERICAN GOVERNMENT EXECUTIVES NETWORK. Application deadline is 4/30. Please see the attachment for details.</span> </span></span></div>\n<div>3. The Council of Asian and Pacific Americans in Michign is sponsoring an Asian Cultural Dance Performance Show \"Splendor of the East\" on Friday, May 14, 2010 at 7 p.m. at Ford Community\nand Performing Arts Center in Dearborn. The organizer is looking for 2-3 volunteers from Chinese organization for the following work on May14:</div>\n<div>* food set up for the VIP reception</div>\n<div>* usher guests into the auditorium</div>\n<div>* runners for program participants</div>\n<div>* Others</div>\n<div>\n<div><span>There will be discount in admission </span><span>( or possible free admission) for volunteers. </span>This is a good opoortunity to let youngsters to participate in this international cultural event. Please contact \"Sue Sung\" [<a href=\"mailto:sue.sung@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">sue.sung@gmail.com</a>] if you are interested. The poster is too big to send, you may find more details from the website <a title=\"http://capa-mi.org/\" href=\"http://capa-mi.org/\" target=\"_blank\">capa-mi.org</a></div>\n</div>\n<div>4.  Big Coming Event that I encourage all families to participate:</div>\n<div>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n\n<strong>*</strong><strong>Taiwanese American Heritage Week Cultural Fair*</strong>\n<strong>\nFriday</strong>, May 7th, 6:30-8pm @ Duderstadt Center Connector, The University of Michigan North Campus, 2281 Bonisteel Boulevard, Ann Arbor\n<strong>Saturday</strong>, May 8th, 10am-3pm @ Sheraton Hotel, 21111 Haggerty Road, Novi.\n\nIn celebration of Taiwanese American Heritage Week, all are invited to join the unique opportunity to see cultural presentations by renowned Taiwanese folk artisans in:\n* Lion Head (used in Lion Dance) Painting\n* Hand Puppetry\n* Dough Figuring Sculpture\n* Sugar Sculpture\n* Gourd Carving\n* Paper Umbrella Painting\n* Sculpture using tree bark, leaves, and other natural materials..\n* Silhouette paper cutting\nHands-on activities available for children and adults.   For details and  directions, please visit <a title=\"http://www.mitai.org\" href=\"http://www.mitai.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.mitai.org</a>.\n\nFREE. Donations welcome to help cover the material fees.</div>\n<div>++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n\nHave a great week!</div>\n<div>Best Regards</div>\n<div>Alex Tang</div>\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 4/17/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','58-revision','','','2010-04-16 22:49:22','2010-04-17 02:49:22','',58,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=63',0,'revision','',0),(65,1,'2010-04-16 22:55:54','2010-04-17 02:55:54','<div>Dear MCS parents,</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>This week we will have speech contest during the regular class hour and therefore class is cancelled. I hope every student is ready to perform their best in the contest.</div>\n<div>We are starting the process to nominate vice principal candidate for 2010-2011 school year. Please contact either me or Jessi or Julia if you or your friends are interested in leading MCS to create a better learning environment for our next generation.</div>\n<div>The following are some Chinese community information you maybe interested:</div>\n<div>1. Eric Wu, who used to be a MCS student, is offering a free after school tennis class to MCS students. Attached please find a flyer he passed out. I really appreciate his devotion to serve MCS with his talent. Please contact me if you are interested in attending this tennis training class (limited openings).</div>\n<div>2. There are scholarship opportunities offered by <span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">ASIAN AMERICAN GOVERNMENT EXECUTIVES NETWORK. Application deadline is 4/30. Please see the attachment for details.</span> </span></span></div>\n<div>3. The Council of Asian and Pacific Americans in Michign is sponsoring an Asian Cultural Dance Performance Show \"Splendor of the East\" on Friday, May 14, 2010 at 7 p.m. at Ford Community\nand Performing Arts Center in Dearborn. The organizer is looking for 2-3 volunteers from Chinese organization for the following work on May14:</div>\n<div>* food set up for the VIP reception</div>\n<div>* usher guests into the auditorium</div>\n<div>* runners for program participants</div>\n<div>* Others</div>\n<div>\n<div><span>There will be discount in admission </span><span>( or possible free admission) for volunteers. </span>This is a good opoortunity to let youngsters to participate in this international cultural event. Please contact \"Sue Sung\" [<a href=\"mailto:sue.sung@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">sue.sung@gmail.com</a>] if you are interested. The poster is too big to send, you may find more details from the website <a title=\"http://capa-mi.org/\" href=\"http://capa-mi.org/\" target=\"_blank\">capa-mi.org</a></div>\n</div>\n<div>4.  Big Coming Event that I encourage all families to participate:</div>\n<div>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n\n<strong>*</strong><strong>Taiwanese American Heritage Week Cultural Fair*</strong>\n<strong>\nFriday</strong>, May 7th, 6:30-8pm @ Duderstadt Center Connector, The University of Michigan North Campus, 2281 Bonisteel Boulevard, Ann Arbor\n<strong>Saturday</strong>, May 8th, 10am-3pm @ Sheraton Hotel, 21111 Haggerty Road, Novi.\n\nIn celebration of Taiwanese American Heritage Week, all are invited to join the unique opportunity to see cultural presentations by renowned Taiwanese folk artisans in:\n* Lion Head (used in Lion Dance) Painting\n* Hand Puppetry\n* Dough Figuring Sculpture\n* Sugar Sculpture\n* Gourd Carving\n* Paper Umbrella Painting\n* Sculpture using tree bark, leaves, and other natural materials..\n* Silhouette paper cutting\nHands-on activities available for children and adults.   For details and  directions, please visit <a title=\"http://www.mitai.org\" href=\"http://www.mitai.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.mitai.org</a>.\n\nFREE. Donations welcome to help cover the material fees.</div>\n<div>++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n\nHave a great week!</div>\n<div>Best Regards</div>\n<div>Alex Tang</div>\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<