'','','2010-04-16 22:57:15','2010-04-17 02:57:15','',58,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=67',0,'revision','',0),(68,1,'2010-04-23 06:51:27','2010-04-23 10:51:27','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nWe had an exciting speech contest last week. Personally, I really enjoy the story telling contest. If you recorded videos or took some good pictures during the contest, please contact JauYeu Lai <a href=\"mailto:jauyeulai@yahoo.com\" target=\"_blank\">jauyeulai@yahoo.com</a> and Steven Lien <a href=\"mailto:tengkolien@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">tengkolien@gmail.com</a> so the pics and videos maybe shared to other parents via MCS website.\r\n\r\nOur PTA chair Julia Liu invited Lisa Hou to offer a seminar on \"Life Insurance\" this Saturday. Lisa did an outstanding presentation on \"Education Fund\" a few weeks back and was well received. Please come to the Parents room around 1:45pm to enjoy a lively and detail knowledge sharing from Lisa.\r\n\r\nSeveral parents would like to know whether we could move the school hours from Saturday afternoon to Saturday morning. Attached please find a survey form that requires your participation. Julia Liu will announce the survey results in our 5/1 Parents Assembly.\r\n\r\nI have asked Eric Wu, who volunteered to offer a free tennis class to our students, to come to our school this Saturday to offer more details of the class. Please let me know if your kids plan to attend. Since Madonna U. does not have tennis court, the class will likely to be held at the tennis court at Schoolcraft college.\r\n\r\nWe will have a Parents Assembly on 5/1. One of the agenda item for the Parents Assembly is the election of MCS vice principal. We need everyone to participate. Please mark you calendar to attend this meeting.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 馮安強, 馮宇\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 4/24/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-4242010','','','2010-04-23 06:51:27','2010-04-23 10:51:27','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=68',0,'post','',0),(69,1,'2010-04-23 06:51:08','2010-04-23 10:51:08','Dear MCS parents,\n\nWe had an exciting speech contest last week. Personally, I really enjoy the story telling contest. If you recorded videos or took some good pictures during the contest, please contact JauYeu Lai <a href=\"mailto:jauyeulai@yahoo.com\" target=\"_blank\">jauyeulai@yahoo.com</a> and Steven Lien <a href=\"mailto:tengkolien@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">tengkolien@gmail.com</a> so the pics and videos maybe shared to other parents via MCS website.\n\nOur PTA chair Julia Liu invited Lisa Hou to offer a seminar on \"Life Insurance\" this Saturday. Lisa did an outstanding presentation on \"Education Fund\" a few weeks back and was well received. Please come to the Parents room around 1:45pm to enjoy a lively and detail knowledge sharing from Lisa.\n\nSeveral parents would like to know whether we could move the school hours from Saturday afternoon to Saturday morning. Attached please find a survey form that requires your participation. Julia Liu will announce the survey results in our 5/1 Parents Assembly.\n\nI have asked Eric Wu, who volunteered to offer a free tennis class to our students, to come to our school this Saturday to offer more details of the class. Please let me know if your kids plan to attend. Since Madonna U. does not have tennis court, the class will likely to be held at the tennis court at Schoolcraft college.\n\nWe will have a Parents Assembly on 5/1. One of the agenda item for the Parents Assembly is the election of MCS vice principal. We need everyone to participate. Please mark you calendar to attend this meeting.\n\nParents on duty: 馮安強, 馮宇\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 4/24/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','68-revision','','','2010-04-23 06:51:08','2010-04-23 10:51:08','',68,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=69',0,'revision','',0),(70,1,'2010-04-30 07:37:42','2010-04-30 11:37:42','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\n--- 2nd semester Parents Assembly 5/1 ---\r\nThis is the meeting we will provide a review of school status, future plan and school class schedule survey results. We will also nominate and elect 2010 vice principal if we have enough parents votes. Please participate to exercise your rights and voice your opinions on school activities.\r\n\r\n--- Taiwan Traditional Culture Week 5/7 &amp; 5/8 ---\r\nA word file is attached for details of this activity. Great opportunity to expose our next generations to some traditional cultures! Don\'t miss it.\r\n\r\n--- Free tennis  class offered by Eric Wu ---\r\nFirst class will be held at Schoolcraft college tennis court this Saturday after regular class at 3:45pm. Experienced or not, you may come to the class to start enjoying tennis with a passionate coach. Eric will bring some of his used tennis rackets for those who don\'t have rackets yet. He will bring the tennis balls too. Note, class will be postponed to next week if we got a bad weather.\r\n\r\n--- Life Insurance Presentation ---\r\nLast week our ex-principal Lisa Hou made a detail presentation on life insurance. Thanks for Lisa\'s dedicated effort! The presentation material is now posted on MCS website for your reference.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 江政承, 賴哲琛\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 5/1/2010 - Parents Assembly',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-512010-parents-assembly','','','2010-04-30 07:37:42','2010-04-30 11:37:42','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=70',0,'post','',0),(71,1,'2010-04-30 07:37:38','2010-04-30 11:37:38','Dear MCS parents,\n\n--- 2nd semester Parents Assembly 5/1 ---\nThis is the meeting we will provide a review of school status, future plan and school class schedule survey results. We will also nominate and elect 2010 vice principal if we have enough parents votes. Please participate to exercise your rights and voice your opinions on school activities.\n\n--- Taiwan Traditional Culture Week 5/7 &amp; 5/8 ---\nA word file is attached for details of this activity. Great opportunity to expose our next generations to some traditional cultures! Don\'t miss it.\n\n--- Free tennis  class offered by Eric Wu ---\nFirst class will be held at Schoolcraft college tennis court this Saturday after regular class at 3:45pm. Experienced or not, you may come to the class to start enjoying tennis with a passionate coach. Eric will bring some of his used tennis rackets for those who don\'t have rackets yet. He will bring the tennis balls too. Note, class will be postponed to next week if we got a bad weather.\n\n--- Life Insurance Presentation ---\nLast week our ex-principal Lisa Hou made a detail presentation on life insurance. Thanks for Lisa\'s dedicated effort! The presentation material is now posted on MCS website for your reference.\n\nParents on duty: 江政承, 賴哲琛\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 5/1/2010 - Parents Assembly',0,'','inherit','open','open','','70-revision','','','2010-04-30 07:37:38','2010-04-30 11:37:38','',70,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=71',0,'revision','',0),(72,1,'2010-05-06 22:56:42','2010-05-07 02:56:42','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\n--- Cast your vote for MCS 2010 Vice Principal ---\r\n\r\nPlease cast your vote to our VP candidate <span style=\"font-size: small;\">呂宗龍  (</span>Chung-Long Lu) by this Saturday via e-mail or fill in and return the ballot to your parent representative. I\'m impressed by Chung-Long\'s introduction of himself and his willingness to devote time and effort to our school. Let\'s all give him a big hand!\r\n\r\n--- 5/8 Taiwan Traditional Culture Week ---\r\n\r\nReminder, this event is from 10am to 3pm at Novi Sheraton Hotel this Saturday. Lion dance team will perform at 10am. Invite your friends to enjoy this rare opportunity to learn traditional culture demonstrated by national experts from Taiwan.\r\n\r\n--- Exchange of unwanted items (books, toys, household items...) at parents lounge ---\r\n\r\nWe all have some surplus or used items that other families may find better use. Why not take them to our school to share with other parents this Saturday? Young families maybe interested in the used books or baby stuff that your kids has grown out of. Let\'s start the sharing this Saturday!\r\n\r\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class ---\r\n\r\nEric Wu conduct the first tennis class last Saturday after school at schoolcraft tennis court. There are 12 students attended the training for over an hour. Eric did teaching on basic stroke for forehand and backhand. The students are divided into experienced and beginner groups. They made good practices. The class will be held at same place and same time this weekend.\r\n\r\n--- Take a look of speech contest photos posted on MCS website ---\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>\r\n\r\n--- Hunan-Hunan will deliver your food orders this week ---\r\n\r\n如有家长想訂东西請电(313)389-0939\r\n\r\n--- parents on duty ---\r\n\r\n楊耀光\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 5/8/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-582010','','','2010-05-06 22:56:42','2010-05-07 02:56:42','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=72',0,'post','',0),(73,1,'2010-05-06 22:56:38','2010-05-07 02:56:38','Dear MCS parents,\n\n--- Cast your vote for MCS 2010 Vice Principal ---\n\nPlease cast your vote to our VP candidate <span style=\"font-size: small;\">呂宗龍  (</span>Chung-Long Lu) by this Saturday via e-mail or fill in and return the ballot to your parent representative. I\'m impressed by Chung-Long\'s introduction of himself and his willingness to devote time and effort to our school. Let\'s all give him a big hand!\n\n--- 5/8 Taiwan Traditional Culture Week ---\n\nReminder, this event is from 10am to 3pm at Novi Sheraton Hotel this Saturday. Lion dance team will perform at 10am. Invite your friends to enjoy this rare opportunity to learn traditional culture demonstrated by national experts from Taiwan.\n\n--- Exchange of unwanted items (books, toys, household items...) at parents lounge ---\n\nWe all have some surplus or used items that other families may find better use. Why not take them to our school to share with other parents this Saturday? Young families maybe interested in the used books or baby stuff that your kids has grown out of. Let\'s start the sharing this Saturday!\n\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class ---\n\nEric Wu conduct the first tennis class last Saturday after school at schoolcraft tennis court. There are 12 students attended the training for over an hour. Eric did teaching on basic stroke for forehand and backhand. The students are divided into experienced and beginner groups. They made good practices. The class will be held at same place and same time this weekend.\n\n--- Take a look of speech contest photos posted on MCS website ---\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>\n\n--- Hunan-Hunan will deliver your food orders this week ---\n\n如有家长想訂东西請电(313)389-0939\n\n--- parents on duty ---\n\n楊耀光\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 5/8/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','72-revision','','','2010-05-06 22:56:38','2010-05-07 02:56:38','',72,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=73',0,'revision','',0),(74,1,'2010-05-14 23:57:38','2010-05-15 03:57:38','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nCongratulate to <strong>呂宗龍 Chung-Long Lu </strong>to become 2010 Vice principal! I believe he and Jesse will make a good team<strong> </strong>to lead our school next year.<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\nSome of our students, the speech contest winners, will participate in the Inter-School Speech Contest at Ann Arbor this Saturday. Good luck to our teams!\r\n\r\nReminder, it\'s coming to the end of this semester. Don\'t forget that we have several events coming: Word Recognition Contest (認字比賽) , Chinese Writing Contest (作文比賽) and 弟子規 recitation. As announced earlier, students may register with their class teachers to recite 弟子規 within the last two weeks of the school. All awards will be presented in the Graduation Ceremony on 6/12.\r\n\r\nSome information to share:\r\n\r\n--- 全美徵文比賽 ---\r\n\r\n全美中文學校聯合會，期許全美各地中文學校之學生，運用其個人習得之中文寫作能力，在觀察，判斷，思考等方面，銓釋出個人獨特見解的創作才華。為了提高中文學習者之寫作能力，在全美各地舉辦中文作文徵文比賽。\r\n\r\nDetails of this event and registration forms are posted on MCS website.\r\n\r\n--- Taiwan Automotive International Forum &amp; Exhibition ---\r\n\r\n密西根國建學術聯誼會 <tt>MCAPA is actively working with ITRI and APACC to support the 2010 Taiwan  Automotive International Forum &amp; Exhibition. TAIFE 2010, a two-day  exhibition of Smart Green Vehicle Technologies &amp; Products developed in  Taiwan, will be held at Sheraton Detroit Novi on June 21 - 22. This is one of  the largest exhibits Taiwan has done overseas to showcase the superior  capabilities of EV supply chain.\r\n\r\nYou are cordially invited to a  complimentary breakfast, lunch, or dinner briefing. Please review the attached  and register for this exciting, eye-opening event.\r\n</tt><a href=\"http://www.apacc.net/mc/community/eventdetails.do?eventId=266748&amp;orgId=apacc&amp;recurringId=0\" target=\"_blank\"><tt>http://www.apacc.net/mc/community/eventdetails.do?eventId=266748&amp;orgId=apacc&amp;recurringId=0\r\n</tt></a>\r\n\r\n--- <strong>2010</strong><strong>年密西根青少年</strong><strong> </strong><strong>中文</strong><strong>民俗技藝夏令營</strong> Michigan Chinese Youth Summer Camps: Details posted on MCS website ---\r\n\r\n--- Eric Wu tennis class ---\r\nAfter school at Schoolcraft college tennis court as long as weather permits.\r\n\r\n--- Parents on duty ---\r\nPhil Ye, 何立人\r\n\r\n--- Free Stuff Sharing ---\r\nLast week some parents brought in used books, magazines to share with other parents. Most books are gone. We will continue this activity every week.\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal,  MCS','MCS Communication - 5/15/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-5152010','','','2010-05-14 23:57:38','2010-05-15 03:57:38','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=74',0,'post','',0),(75,1,'2010-05-14 23:57:07','2010-05-15 03:57:07','Dear MCS parents,\n\nCongratulate to <strong>呂宗龍 Chung-Long Lu </strong>to become 2010 Vice principal! I believe he and Jesse will make a good team<strong> </strong>to lead our school next year.<strong>\n</strong>\nSome of our students, the speech contest winners, will participate in the Inter-School Speech Contest at Ann Arbor this Saturday. Good luck to our teams!\n\nReminder, it\'s coming to the end of this semester. Don\'t forget that we have several events coming: Word Recognition Contest (認字比賽) , Chinese Writing Contest (作文比賽) and 弟子規 recitation. As announced earlier, students may register with their class teachers to recite 弟子規 within the last two weeks of the school. All awards will be presented in the Graduation Ceremony on 6/12.\n\nSome information to share:\n\n--- 全美徵文比賽 ---\n\n全美中文學校聯合會，期許全美各地中文學校之學生，運用其個人習得之中文寫作能力，在觀察，判斷，思考等方面，銓釋出個人獨特見解的創作才華。為了提高中文學習者之寫作能力，在全美各地舉辦中文作文徵文比賽。\n\nDetails of this event and registration forms are posted on MCS website.\n\n--- Taiwan Automotive International Forum &amp; Exhibition ---\n\n密西根國建學術聯誼會 <tt>MCAPA is actively working with ITRI and APACC to support the 2010 Taiwan  Automotive International Forum &amp; Exhibition. TAIFE 2010, a two-day  exhibition of Smart Green Vehicle Technologies &amp; Products developed in  Taiwan, will be held at Sheraton Detroit Novi on June 21 - 22. This is one of  the largest exhibits Taiwan has done overseas to showcase the superior  capabilities of EV supply chain.\n\nYou are cordially invited to a  complimentary breakfast, lunch, or dinner briefing. Please review the attached  and register for this exciting, eye-opening event.\n</tt><a href=\"http://www.apacc.net/mc/community/eventdetails.do?eventId=266748&amp;orgId=apacc&amp;recurringId=0\" target=\"_blank\"><tt>http://www.apacc.net/mc/community/eventdetails.do?eventId=266748&amp;orgId=apacc&amp;recurringId=0\n</tt></a>\n\n--- <strong>2010</strong><strong>年密西根青少年</strong><strong> </strong><strong>中文</strong><strong>民俗技藝夏令營</strong> Michigan Chinese Youth Summer Camps: Details posted on MCS website ---\n\n--- Eric Wu tennis class ---\nAfter school at Schoolcraft college tennis court as long as weather permits.\n\n--- Parents on duty ---\nPhil Ye, 何立人\n\n--- Free Stuff Sharing ---\nLast week some parents brought in used books, magazines to share with other parents. Most books are gone. We will continue this activity every week.\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal,  MCS','MCS Communication - 5/15/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','74-revision','','','2010-05-14 23:57:07','2010-05-15 03:57:07','',74,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=75',0,'revision','',0),(76,1,'2010-05-21 15:02:42','2010-05-21 19:02:42','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nWe will start fall semester pre-registration this week. In 2010, we are planning to offer 12 classes --<strong> Pre-K, K, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 8, Senior, M10, M12 &amp; CSL.</strong> Please note that current students who miss the pre-registration will be charged $20 late fee (same amount as before). You may download and fill out the new registration form from MCS website.\r\n\r\nLast week our students competed in the Inter-School Chinese Speech Contest hosted by Ann Arbor Chinese School. We are very proud of the performance of all our students. Congratulate to the following winners from our school:\r\n\r\n演講比賽：\r\n\r\n[第一組] 第一名江秉陽；第二名盛嘉詰；第三名鄭羽翔。\r\n\r\n[第二組] 第一名魏郁安\r\n\r\n[第三組] 第一名王淨慧\r\n\r\n看圖說故事比賽：\r\n\r\n[第七組]          第二名    陳楷文,王淨德,鄺紹耘；\r\n\r\n[第八組]          第三名：鄒佩成,呂詠恩,邱 晧。\r\n\r\nFor students who didn\'t win, don\'t be discouraged. There are always opportunities in the future. Attached is a news release issued by AnnArbor Chinese School. Thanks to our ex-principal Lisa Hou, she took some pictures during the contest and we will post them on our website. We also want to thank our 教務主任 羅庭偉, who spent a lot of time coordinating the whole speech constest event. We also want to thank teachers who took their personal time to train these students before the competition:    There are some new community information posted on our website. You may find it interesteing to you. From time to time we will post photos and articles to share with you. So don\'t forget to visit MCS website.   -\r\n\r\n-- Hunan-Hunan will deliver your food orders this week.\r\n\r\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class continues at schoolcraft college tennis court afterschool.\r\n\r\n--- Parents on duty: 劉蔚芝, 徐劼池\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/A十七屆密西根州中文學校校際演講比賽.pdf\">A十七屆密西根州中文學校校際演講比賽</a>\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\n\r\nAlex Tang Principal, MCS','MCS Communication - 5/22/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-5222010','','','2010-05-21 15:02:42','2010-05-21 19:02:42','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=76',0,'post','',0),(77,1,'2010-05-21 15:01:17','2010-05-21 19:01:17','','A十七屆密西根州中文學校校際演講比賽',0,'','inherit','open','open','','a%e5%8d%81%e4%b8%83%e5%b1%86%e5%af%86%e8%a5%bf%e6%a0%b9%e5%b7%9e%e4%b8%ad%e6%96%87%e5%ad%b8%e6%a0%a1%e6%a0%a1%e9%9a%9b%e6%bc%94%e8%ac%9b%e6%af%94%e8%b3%bd','','','2010-05-21 15:01:17','2010-05-21 19:01:17','',76,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/A十七屆密西根州中文學校校際演講比賽.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(78,1,'2010-05-21 15:02:24','2010-05-21 19:02:24','Dear MCS parents,\n\nWe will start fall semester pre-registration this week. In 2010, we are planning to offer 12 classes --<strong> Pre-K, K, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 8, Senior, M10, M12 &amp; CSL.</strong> Please note that current students who miss the pre-registration will be charged $20 late fee (same amount as before). You may download and fill out the new registration form from MCS website.\n\nLast week our students competed in the Inter-School Chinese Speech Contest hosted by Ann Arbor Chinese School. We are very proud of the performance of all our students. Congratulate to the following winners from our school:\n\n演講比賽：\n\n[第一組] 第一名江秉陽；第二名盛嘉詰；第三名鄭羽翔。\n\n[第二組] 第一名魏郁安\n\n[第三組] 第一名王淨慧\n\n看圖說故事比賽：\n\n[第七組]          第二名    陳楷文,王淨德,鄺紹耘；\n\n[第八組]          第三名：鄒佩成,呂詠恩,邱 晧。\n\nFor students who didn\'t win, don\'t be discouraged. There are always opportunities in the future. Attached is a news release issued by AnnArbor Chinese School. Thanks to our ex-principal Lisa Hou, she took some pictures during the contest and we will post them on our website. We also want to thank our 教務主任 羅庭偉, who spent a lot of time coordinating the whole speech constest event. We also want to thank teachers who took their personal time to train these students before the competition:    There are some new community information posted on our website. You may find it interesteing to you. From time to time we will post photos and articles to share with you. So don\'t forget to visit MCS website.   -\n\n-- Hunan-Hunan will deliver your food orders this week.\n\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class continues at schoolcraft college tennis court afterschool.\n\n--- Parents on duty: 劉蔚芝, 徐劼池\n\nBest Regards Alex Tang Principal, MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/A十七屆密西根州中文學校校際演講比賽.pdf\">A十七屆密西根州中文學校校際演講比賽</a>','MCS Communication - 5/22/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','76-revision','','','2010-05-21 15:02:24','2010-05-21 19:02:24','',76,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=78',0,'revision','',0),(79,1,'2010-06-03 23:46:49','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Dear MCS parents,\n\nI hope you all have enjoyed a wonderful Memorial weekend. Now it\'s time to get back to school. This weekend we have the following events:\n\n--- Pre-registration for 2010 fall semester ---\nPlease register your kids this Saturday. Don\'t put it off till fall semester. A $20 registration fee will be applied during fall registration period.\n\n--- Word recognition &amp; writing contest will be conducted for each class --\nHelp your kids to get prepared. Top rank students from the contest will be rewarded by teacher in each class.\n\n--- Jimmy Yang, our ex-PTA chair, will make a presentation related to  his work at Taiwan --\nPlease review the attached file for details. Let\'s all show Jimmy our welcome by joining this presentation!\n\n--- Last week to participate in 弟子規 recitation ---\nThere are 6 sections in  弟子規. Students may get $10 award for each section  he or she recited. Students who may recite the complete 弟子規 will be  awarded $100. Recitation may begin on the week of 5/15. Scholarship will  be awarded during the school graduation ceremony. Here’s the link to an ROC government website that has very helpful  teaching material of 弟子規: <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/\" target=\"_blank\">http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/</a>. Each student may go to his or her teacher to recite during class break.\n\n--- Free stuff exchange ---\nBring in your used books, magazines, toys, sports equipments,... to pass to other parents for best reuse.\n\n--- Parents on duty: 車國榮, 邵恩棟 ---\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 6/5/2010',0,'','draft','closed','open','','','','','2010-06-03 23:46:49','2010-06-04 03:46:49','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=79',0,'post','',0),(80,1,'2010-06-03 23:48:35','2010-06-04 03:48:35','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI hope you all have enjoyed a wonderful Memorial weekend. Now it\'s time to get back to school. This weekend we have the following events:\r\n\r\n--- Pre-registration for 2010 fall semester ---\r\nPlease register your kids this Saturday. Don\'t put it off till fall semester. A $20 registration fee will be applied during fall registration period.\r\n\r\n--- Word recognition &amp; writing contest will be conducted for each class --\r\nHelp your kids to get prepared. Top rank students from the contest will be rewarded by teacher in each class.\r\n\r\n--- Jimmy Yang, our ex-PTA chair, will make a presentation related to  his work at Taiwan --\r\nPlease review the attached file for details. Let\'s all show Jimmy our welcome by joining this presentation!\r\n\r\n--- Last week to participate in 弟子規 recitation ---\r\nThere are 6 sections in  弟子規. Students may get $10 award for each section  he or she recited. Students who may recite the complete 弟子規 will be  awarded $100. Recitation may begin on the week of 5/15. Scholarship will  be awarded during the school graduation ceremony. Here’s the link to an ROC government website that has very helpful  teaching material of 弟子規: <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/\" target=\"_blank\">http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/</a>. Each student may go to his or her teacher to recite during class break.\r\n\r\n--- Free stuff exchange ---\r\nBring in your used books, magazines, toys, sports equipments,... to pass to other parents for best reuse.\r\n\r\n--- Parents on duty: 車國榮, 邵恩棟 ---\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 6/5/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-652010','','','2010-06-03 23:48:47','2010-06-04 03:48:47','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=80',0,'post','',0),(81,1,'2010-06-03 23:48:35','2010-06-04 03:48:35','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nI hope you all have enjoyed a wonderful Memorial weekend. Now it\'s time to get back to school. This weekend we have the following events:\r\n\r\n--- Pre-registration for 2010 fall semester ---\r\nPlease register your kids this Saturday. Don\'t put it off till fall semester. A $20 registration fee will be applied during fall registration period.\r\n\r\n--- Word recognition &amp; writing contest will be conducted for each class --\r\nHelp your kids to get prepared. Top rank students from the contest will be rewarded by teacher in each class.\r\n\r\n--- Jimmy Yang, our ex-PTA chair, will make a presentation related to  his work at Taiwan --\r\nPlease review the attached file for details. Let\'s all show Jimmy our welcome by joining this presentation!\r\n\r\n--- Last week to participate in 弟子規 recitation ---\r\nThere are 6 sections in  弟子規. Students may get $10 award for each section  he or she recited. Students who may recite the complete 弟子規 will be  awarded $100. Recitation may begin on the week of 5/15. Scholarship will  be awarded during the school graduation ceremony. Here’s the link to an ROC government website that has very helpful  teaching material of 弟子規: <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/\" target=\"_blank\">http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/</a>. Each student may go to his or her teacher to recite during class break.\r\n\r\n--- Free stuff exchange ---\r\nBring in your used books, magazines, toys, sports equipments,... to pass to other parents for best reuse.\r\n\r\n--- Parents on duty: 車國榮, 邵恩棟 ---\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS','MCS Communication - 6/5/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','80-revision','','','2010-06-03 23:48:35','2010-06-04 03:48:35','',80,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=81',0,'revision','',0),(82,1,'2010-06-11 23:39:15','2010-06-12 03:39:15','Dear MCS parents,\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThis Saturday is the last day of 2009-2010 school year. We will have one hour of class followed with school Commencement at Science Lecture Hall (room 1301) starting 2:30pm. There will be no after-school activity.\r\n\r\nThe graduation ceremony will include presentation of awards for academic performance, attendance, and recitation of 弟子規. I will also turn the school to our 2010 Principal, Mr. Jesse Wei. After the ceremony, we will enjoy some light snacks and refreshment at Take Five Lounge to celebrate the end of the school year.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>In this last MCS communication, I want to thank each staff member  for his/hers dedication to the school. We had wonderful time working together as one team. Thanks!  Also I want to thank all teachers and our PTA chairs Julia Liu and Jim Yang for your supports throughout the year. To all parents, it has been my honor and pleasure to serve you. I believe, with your continuous participation in our school activities, MCS will keep growing and become better and better in the future.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAs usual, we have the following information to share with you:\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n--- This Saturday is last day of pre-registration to waive $20 registration fee ---\r\n\r\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class will continue during summer vacation ---\r\nLocation: Oakland community college tennis court\r\nDate: starting 7/2 Friday, meet once a week\r\nTime: 7pm\r\nThis class is offered to all MCS students for free. You may meet Eric at the class hour to register.\r\n\r\n--- 駐芝加哥台北經濟文化辦事處將提供領務諮詢及收件服務 ---\r\nPlease see attached file\r\n\r\n--- Inter-school Chinese speech contest photos posted on the following link ---\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.gan-photography.com/Events/Events.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.gan-photography.com/Events/Events.htm</a>\r\nThe log in name : CSC\r\npassword : may15\r\nWe thank Kim-Tong Gan from Ann Arbor Chinese School for his great work !\r\n\r\n--- Jim Yang offered an excellent presentation on his current work at Taiwan last Saturday ---\r\n\r\n--- 2010 TAIFE event on 6/21, 6/22 ---\r\nPlease see attached file\r\n\r\n--- Hunan Hunan will deliver Chinese food to school ---\r\n\r\n--- Jessica Lee will deliver 粽子 to school ---\r\n\r\nWish you all have a wonderful summer vacation\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal,  MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/news99.6.09.doc\">news99.6.09</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TAIFE2010_Briefing_2page_Invitation.pdf\">TAIFE2010_Briefing_2page_Invitation</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TAIFE_2010_Flyer.pdf\">TAIFE_2010_Flyer</a>','MCS Communication - 6/12/2010 - Last day of school',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-6122010-last-day-of-school','','','2010-06-11 23:42:10','2010-06-12 03:42:10','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=82',0,'post','',0),(83,1,'2010-06-11 23:37:36','2010-06-12 03:37:36','Dear MCS parents,\n<div>This Saturday is the last day of 2009-2010 school year. We will have one hour of class followed with school Commencement at Science Lecture Hall (room 1301) starting 2:30pm. There will be no after-school activity.\n\nThe graduation ceremony will include presentation of awards for academic performance, attendance, and recitation of 弟子規. I will also turn the school to our 2010 Principal, Mr. Jesse Wei. After the ceremony, we will enjoy some light snacks and refreshment at Take Five Lounge to celebrate the end of the school year.</div>\n<div>\nIn this last MCS communication, I want to thank each staff member  for his/hers dedication to the school. We had wonderful time working together as one team. Thanks!  Also I want to thank all teachers and our PTA chairs Julia Liu and Jim Yang for your supports throughout the year. To all parents, it has been my honor and pleasure to serve you. I believe, with your continuous participation in our school activities, MCS will keep growing and become better and better in the future.</div>\n<div>As usual, we have the following information to share with you:\n\n</div>\n--- This Saturday is last day of pre-registration to waive $20 registration fee ---\n\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class will continue during summer vacation ---\nLocation: Oakland community college tennis court\nDate: starting 7/2 Friday, meet once a week\nTime: 7pm\nThis class is offered to all MCS students for free. You may meet Eric at the class hour to register.\n\n--- 駐芝加哥台北經濟文化辦事處將提供領務諮詢及收件服務 ---\nPlease see attached file\n\n--- Inter-school Chinese speech contest photos posted on the following link ---\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.gan-photography.com/Events/Events.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.gan-photography.com/Events/Events.htm</a>\nThe log in name : CSC\npassword : may15\nWe thank Kim-Tong Gan from Ann Arbor Chinese School for his great work !\n\n--- Jim Yang offered an excellent presentation on his current work at Taiwan last Saturday ---\n\n--- 2010 TAIFE event on 6/21, 6/22 ---\nPlease see attached file\n\n--- Hunan Hunan will deliver Chinese food to school ---\n\n--- Jessica Lee will deliver 粽子 to school ---\n\nWish you all have a wonderful summer vacation\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal,  MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 6/12/2010 - Last day of school',0,'','inherit','open','open','','82-revision','','','2010-06-11 23:37:36','2010-06-12 03:37:36','',82,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=83',0,'revision','',0),(84,1,'2010-06-11 23:41:21','2010-06-12 03:41:21','Dear MCS parents,\n<div>\n\nThis Saturday is the last day of 2009-2010 school year. We will have one hour of class followed with school Commencement at Science Lecture Hall (room 1301) starting 2:30pm. There will be no after-school activity.\n\nThe graduation ceremony will include presentation of awards for academic performance, attendance, and recitation of 弟子規. I will also turn the school to our 2010 Principal, Mr. Jesse Wei. After the ceremony, we will enjoy some light snacks and refreshment at Take Five Lounge to celebrate the end of the school year.\n\n</div>\n<div>In this last MCS communication, I want to thank each staff member  for his/hers dedication to the school. We had wonderful time working together as one team. Thanks!  Also I want to thank all teachers and our PTA chairs Julia Liu and Jim Yang for your supports throughout the year. To all parents, it has been my honor and pleasure to serve you. I believe, with your continuous participation in our school activities, MCS will keep growing and become better and better in the future.</div>\n<div>\n\nAs usual, we have the following information to share with you:\n\n</div>\n--- This Saturday is last day of pre-registration to waive $20 registration fee ---\n\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class will continue during summer vacation ---\nLocation: Oakland community college tennis court\nDate: starting 7/2 Friday, meet once a week\nTime: 7pm\nThis class is offered to all MCS students for free. You may meet Eric at the class hour to register.\n\n--- 駐芝加哥台北經濟文化辦事處將提供領務諮詢及收件服務 ---\nPlease see attached file\n\n--- Inter-school Chinese speech contest photos posted on the following link ---\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.gan-photography.com/Events/Events.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.gan-photography.com/Events/Events.htm</a>\nThe log in name : CSC\npassword : may15\nWe thank Kim-Tong Gan from Ann Arbor Chinese School for his great work !\n\n--- Jim Yang offered an excellent presentation on his current work at Taiwan last Saturday ---\n\n--- 2010 TAIFE event on 6/21, 6/22 ---\nPlease see attached file\n\n--- Hunan Hunan will deliver Chinese food to school ---\n\n--- Jessica Lee will deliver 粽子 to school ---\n\nWish you all have a wonderful summer vacation\n\nBest Regards\nAlex Tang\nPrincipal,  MCS\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/news99.6.09.doc\">news99.6.09</a>','MCS Communication - 6/12/2010 - Last day of school',0,'','inherit','open','open','','82-autosave','','','2010-06-11 23:41:21','2010-06-12 03:41:21','',82,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=84',0,'revision','',0),(85,1,'2010-06-11 23:41:08','2010-06-12 03:41:08','','news99.6.09',0,'','inherit','open','open','','news99-6-09','','','2010-06-11 23:41:08','2010-06-12 03:41:08','',82,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/news99.6.09.doc',0,'attachment','application/msword',0),(86,1,'2010-06-11 23:41:35','2010-06-12 03:41:35','','TAIFE2010_Briefing_2page_Invitation',0,'','inherit','open','open','','taife2010_briefing_2page_invitation','','','2010-06-11 23:41:35','2010-06-12 03:41:35','',82,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TAIFE2010_Briefing_2page_Invitation.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(87,1,'2010-06-11 23:42:02','2010-06-12 03:42:02','','TAIFE_2010_Flyer',0,'','inherit','open','open','','taife_2010_flyer','','','2010-06-11 23:42:02','2010-06-12 03:42:02','',82,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/TAIFE_2010_Flyer.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(88,1,'2010-06-11 23:39:15','2010-06-12 03:39:15','Dear MCS parents,\r\n<div>This Saturday is the last day of 2009-2010 school year. We will have one hour of class followed with school Commencement at Science Lecture Hall (room 1301) starting 2:30pm. There will be no after-school activity.\r\n\r\nThe graduation ceremony will include presentation of awards for academic performance, attendance, and recitation of 弟子規. I will also turn the school to our 2010 Principal, Mr. Jesse Wei. After the ceremony, we will enjoy some light snacks and refreshment at Take Five Lounge to celebrate the end of the school year.</div>\r\n<div>\r\nIn this last MCS communication, I want to thank each staff member  for his/hers dedication to the school. We had wonderful time working together as one team. Thanks!  Also I want to thank all teachers and our PTA chairs Julia Liu and Jim Yang for your supports throughout the year. To all parents, it has been my honor and pleasure to serve you. I believe, with your continuous participation in our school activities, MCS will keep growing and become better and better in the future.</div>\r\n<div>As usual, we have the following information to share with you:\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n--- This Saturday is last day of pre-registration to waive $20 registration fee ---\r\n\r\n--- Eric Wu\'s tennis class will continue during summer vacation ---\r\nLocation: Oakland community college tennis court\r\nDate: starting 7/2 Friday, meet once a week\r\nTime: 7pm\r\nThis class is offered to all MCS students for free. You may meet Eric at the class hour to register.\r\n\r\n--- 駐芝加哥台北經濟文化辦事處將提供領務諮詢及收件服務 ---\r\nPlease see attached file\r\n\r\n--- Inter-school Chinese speech contest photos posted on the following link ---\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.gan-photography.com/Events/Events.htm\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.gan-photography.com/Events/Events.htm</a>\r\nThe log in name : CSC\r\npassword : may15\r\nWe thank Kim-Tong Gan from Ann Arbor Chinese School for his great work !\r\n\r\n--- Jim Yang offered an excellent presentation on his current work at Taiwan last Saturday ---\r\n\r\n--- 2010 TAIFE event on 6/21, 6/22 ---\r\nPlease see attached file\r\n\r\n--- Hunan Hunan will deliver Chinese food to school ---\r\n\r\n--- Jessica Lee will deliver 粽子 to school ---\r\n\r\nWish you all have a wonderful summer vacation\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal,  MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 6/12/2010 - Last day of school',0,'','inherit','open','open','','82-revision-2','','','2010-06-11 23:39:15','2010-06-12 03:39:15','',82,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=88',0,'revision','',0),(89,1,'2010-09-16 23:02:11','2010-09-17 03:02:11','Dear MCS Parents,\r\n\r\nThanks for everyone\'s support, we had a good starting of 2010-2011 school year. We had balloons to celebrate the first day of school, had signs in parking lot and hallway to direct new comers, organized parents lounge and made registration, enrollment and donation clear and easy to find. We also had food vendor sold lunch box to those who were hungry or got some delicious food for future.\r\n\r\nIf you know any family has interest to learn Chinese, please don\'t hestiate to tell them about our school. We have class from Pre-K to 10<sup>th</sup> grade and CSL. We are offering $50.00 referral award to appreciate your efforts.\r\n\r\nWe had parents representatives from each class elected during first day of school. Will have 2010-2011 PTA Chairperson election this Saturday.\r\n\r\nThanks to Lisa Hou\'s coordination and all MCS families’ contribution. We collected total $477.00 at the end of first day and gave the donation to local coordinator- James Ma who will send the donation to Tao\'s family in Taiwan .\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Upcoming Events</span></strong>\r\n\r\n(1)     Moon Festival is approaching and we will have moon cake for all students and teachers this Saturday (9/18)\r\n\r\n(2)     Extra curriculums will start this Saturday (9/18). If you haven’t signed up for your child/children, please stop by parents lounge during school hours to see what classes we have for this year.\r\n\r\n(3)     All new elected parents rep., please come to parents lounge at 1:40 pm this Saturday (9/18) for a brief meeting and election\r\n\r\n(4)     Teachers meeting this Saturday (9/18) at 3:30 pm room #2415\r\n\r\n(5)     Free adult <strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (注音符號) </strong>class enrollment at parents lounge. Class starts on 10/2\r\n\r\n(6)     Home coming dress sale event 9/18 &amp; 9/25 from 1:30 to 3:00 pm. see attached flyer.\r\n\r\n(7)     We will have fall parents assembly on 9/25\r\n\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Newsletters - 9/18/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletters-9182010','','','2010-09-16 23:02:11','2010-09-17 03:02:11','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=89',0,'post','',0),(90,1,'2010-09-16 23:02:06','2010-09-17 03:02:06','Dear MCS Parents,\n\nThanks for everyone\'s support, we had a good starting of 2010-2011 school year. We had balloons to celebrate the first day of school, had signs in parking lot and hallway to direct new comers, organized parents lounge and made registration, enrollment and donation clear and easy to find. We also had food vendor sold lunch box to those who were hungry or got some delicious food for future.\n\nIf you know any family has interest to learn Chinese, please don\'t hestiate to tell them about our school. We have class from Pre-K to 10<sup>th</sup> grade and CSL. We are offering $50.00 referral award to appreciate your efforts.\n\nWe had parents representatives from each class elected during first day of school. Will have 2010-2011 PTA Chairperson election this Saturday.\n\nThanks to Lisa Hou\'s coordination and all MCS families’ contribution. We collected total $477.00 at the end of first day and gave the donation to local coordinator- James Ma who will send the donation to Tao\'s family in Taiwan .\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Upcoming Events</span></strong>\n\n(1)     Moon Festival is approaching and we will have moon cake for all students and teachers this Saturday (9/18)\n\n(2)     Extra curriculums will start this Saturday (9/18). If you haven’t signed up for your child/children, please stop by parents lounge during school hours to see what classes we have for this year.\n\n(3)     All new elected parents rep., please come to parents lounge at 1:40 pm this Saturday (9/18) for a brief meeting and election\n\n(4)     Teachers meeting this Saturday (9/18) at 3:30 pm room #2415\n\n(5)     Free adult <strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (注音符號) </strong>class enrollment at parents lounge. Class starts on 10/2\n\n(6)     Home coming dress sale event 9/18 &amp; 9/25 from 1:30 to 3:00 pm. see attached flyer.\n\n(7)     We will have fall parents assembly on 9/25\n\nJesse Wei\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Newsletters - 9/18/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','89-revision','','','2010-09-16 23:02:06','2010-09-17 03:02:06','',89,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=90',0,'revision','',0),(91,1,'2010-09-16 23:03:15','2010-09-17 03:03:15','Dear MCS Parents,\n\nThanks for everyone\'s support, we had a good starting of 2010-2011 school year. We had balloons to celebrate the first day of school, had signs in parking lot and hallway to direct new comers, organized parents lounge and made registration, enrollment and donation clear and easy to find. We also had food vendor sold lunch box to those who were hungry or got some delicious food for future.\n\nIf you know any family has interest to learn Chinese, please don\'t hestiate to tell them about our school. We have class from Pre-K to 10<sup>th</sup> grade and CSL. We are offering $50.00 referral award to appreciate your efforts.\n\nWe had parents representatives from each class elected during first day of school. Will have 2010-2011 PTA Chairperson election this Saturday.\n\nThanks to Lisa Hou\'s coordination and all MCS families’ contribution. We collected total $477.00 at the end of first day and gave the donation to local coordinator- James Ma who will send the donation to Tao\'s family in Taiwan .\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Upcoming Events</span></strong>\n\n(1)     Moon Festival is approaching and we will have moon cake for all students and teachers this Saturday (9/18)\n\n(2)     Extra curriculums will start this Saturday (9/18). If you haven’t signed up for your child/children, please stop by parents lounge during school hours to see what classes we have for this year.\n\n(3)     All new elected parents rep., please come to parents lounge at 1:40 pm this Saturday (9/18) for a brief meeting and election\n\n(4)     Teachers meeting this Saturday (9/18) at 3:30 pm room #2415\n\n(5)     Free adult <strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (注音符號) </strong>class enrollment at parents lounge. Class starts on 10/2\n\n(6)     Home coming dress sale event 9/18 &amp; 9/25 from 1:30 to 3:00 pm. see attached flyer.\n\n(7)     We will have fall parents assembly on 9/25\n\nJesse Wei\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Newsletters - 9/18/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','89-autosave','','','2010-09-16 23:03:15','2010-09-17 03:03:15','',89,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=91',0,'revision','',0),(92,1,'2010-09-22 22:24:52','2010-09-23 02:24:52','<div><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; font-size: x-small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\"> </span></span>Happy Moon Festival !. First of all, I would like to thank 韓媽媽 baked the moon cake to our students and also provided the free moon cake for all teachers.</div>\r\n<div>(1)Fall Parents meeting 1:30 pm this Saturday at parents lounge. Please be there and we need your input.</div>\r\n<div>(2)<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>Home coming dress, shoes and accessory sale continue on this Saturday</em></span></strong></div>\r\n<div>(3)Free adult <strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (注音符號) </strong>class enrollment at parents lounge. Class starts on 10/2</div>\r\n<div>(4)Food service on Saturday 9/25: QQ 麵包, 雞腿便當, 肉圓 ,炒米粉 ,竽頭酥, 滷雞腿 ....等. Quantity is limited.</div>\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a></div>','MCS Newsletter - 9/25/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','ncs-newsletter-9252010','','','2010-10-28 12:20:16','2010-10-28 16:20:16','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=92',0,'post','',0),(93,1,'2010-09-22 22:24:17','2010-09-23 02:24:17','','NCS Newsletter - 9/25/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','92-revision','','','2010-09-22 22:24:17','2010-09-23 02:24:17','',92,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=93',0,'revision','',0),(94,1,'2010-09-30 22:23:06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">MCS PTA</span></strong>\n\nCongratulations to 陸樹德-new elected 2010-2011 PTA president and 王棋洲 -Vice President.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Budget, Donation &amp; Fun Raising</span></strong>\n\nDuring our parents meeting last week, each staff presented the work plan for school year 2010-2011 and the budget. There are two major reasons caused we face financial challenge. First, this year we had fewer students which is a common concern for all other Chinese Schools in Metro area. Second, we used to have a great amount of our parents’ donation through United Way and this income for sure has come to an end.\n\nMichigan Chinese School is a non-profit organization and your donation can be tax deductible. Every dollar you donate to Michigan Chinese School will be 100% spent on students’ education. If you already have had United Way donation set up at work, you may think about moving all or portion of your donation direct to Michigan Chinese School . You will receive the tax deductible letter from the School. Parent Thomas Sheng suggested setting up an automatic donation from bank account monthly. Our staff is working on this and will keep everyone posted when further information becomes available.\n\nIf you have any fun raising ideas, please contact out staff.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Adult </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Mandarin</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Phonetic Symbols</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> (</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">注音符號</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">) </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">class </span></strong>\n\nClass will start this Saturday at 1:30 pm in room 2407.\n\nInstructor: Lisa Hou\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Evacuation Drill</strong></span>\n\nScheduled on October 9, 2010\nJesse Wei\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Newsletter -10/2/2010',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2010-09-30 22:23:06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=94',0,'post','',0),(95,1,'2010-10-13 23:18:30','2010-10-14 03:18:30','<div><span style=\"font-size: small;\">First of all, we would like to thank <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Brian and Linda Shu</span></strong> who donate their referral cash award to school. </span></div>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fire Drill</span></strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Just a reminder, we will have our annual fire drill this Saturday. All students, teachers and parents who are on campus must participate this drill. See attached map for stair near by your classroom. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Directory Advertisements</span></strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">If you know anyone who is interested to have advertisements on our directory, please talk to any staff. This could be a helpful income for school.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Hunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Jesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School</span>','MCS Newsletter -10/9/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-10162010','','','2010-10-13 23:21:44','2010-10-14 03:21:44','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=95',0,'post','',0),(96,1,'2010-10-13 23:18:05','2010-10-14 03:18:05','','MCS Newsletter -10/16/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','95-revision','','','2010-10-13 23:18:05','2010-10-14 03:18:05','',95,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=96',0,'revision','',0),(97,1,'2010-10-13 23:18:30','2010-10-14 03:18:30','Donation\r\n\r\nThanks to Poyu &amp; Limei Tsou\'s generous donation to Michigan Chinese School .\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFire Drill\r\n\r\nWe had a very successful fire drill last week. In case there is an emergency in the future, please follow the path to a safe location.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFund Raising\r\n\r\nQQ bakery.  Starts at 1:15 pm this Saturday 10/16.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSpecial Event\r\n\r\n(1)   MCAPA 密西根國建學術聯誼會2010 年會邀請函\r\n\r\n– see attached flyer \"MCAPA2010_80-20_v3.pdf\"\r\n\r\n(2)   第一屆華文文化歌唱觀摩實施辦法 – see attached file \"第一屆華文文化歌唱觀摩實施辦法.doc\"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEmployment Opportunity\r\n\r\nIndiana University Bloomington .  The Department of East Asian Languages &amp; Cultures seeks to fill a full-time lecturer position in Chinese language to begin in fall 2011.\r\n\r\nSee attached file \"Employment.doc\"\r\n\r\n\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newsletter -10/16/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','95-revision-2','','','2010-10-13 23:18:30','2010-10-14 03:18:30','',95,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=97',0,'revision','',0),(98,1,'2010-10-13 23:22:27','2010-10-14 03:22:27','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Donation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Poyu &amp; Limei Tsou\'s generous donation to Michigan Chinese School .\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fire Drill</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had a very successful fire drill last week. In case there is an emergency in the future, please follow the path to a safe location.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\r\n\r\nQQ bakery.  Starts at 1:15 pm this Saturday 10/16.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Special Event</span></strong>\r\n\r\n(1)   MCAPA 密西根國建學術聯誼會<strong>2010 </strong>年會邀請函\r\n\r\n– see attached flyer \"<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">MCAPA2010_80-20_v3.pdf</span>\"\r\n\r\n(2)   第一屆華文文化歌唱觀摩實施辦法 – see attached file \"<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">第一屆華文文化歌唱觀摩實施辦法.doc\"</span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Employment Opportunity</span></strong>\r\n\r\nIndiana University Bloomington .  The Department of East Asian Languages &amp; Cultures seeks to fill a full-time lecturer position in Chinese language to begin in fall 2011.\r\n\r\nSee attached file \"<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Employment.doc</span>\"\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newsletter -10/16/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-10162010-2','','','2010-10-13 23:22:27','2010-10-14 03:22:27','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=98',0,'post','',0),(99,1,'2010-10-13 23:22:06','2010-10-14 03:22:06','','MCS Newsletter -10/16/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','98-revision','','','2010-10-13 23:22:06','2010-10-14 03:22:06','',98,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=99',0,'revision','',0),(100,1,'2010-10-22 22:19:13','2010-10-23 02:19:13','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Lisa Hou\'s(侯珞怡) dedicated hard work to provide free teaching about <strong><strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (</strong></strong><strong><strong>注音符號</strong></strong><strong><strong>)</strong></strong> to MCS parents. School will send out survey to those adult students and if there is a need, we will consider offering a new tuition based adult CSL class.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Budget</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAfter parents meeting on 9/25/2010, some of you show the concern about our school budget not balanced from previous school year. There was a different between school account balance on 6/30/2010 and bank statement at that time. Jointed efforts was made by 2009-2010 Principal Tang (唐宗堯), current staff Jessica Lee (陳惠昭)and Chih-Wen Pai (白志文) and finally we have balanced the budget. When MCS started offering Ma Li-Ping classes back to several years ago, initially school purchased more teaching material than actually need in order to get the volume discount. At that time school counted it as an asset. Ideally, we will have to offset it when it was sold, but school counted it as an income. Therefore, there is a difference between school balance sheet and bank statement. We will have this issue corrected this year. We also will present this to parents Rep. during New Year Party preparation meeting (新年晚會籌備會議) scheduled on Nov.6. Everyone is welcomed to attend.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBased on our survey from each class, the majority prefer to have school wide Halloween Party as usual. We will have our 2010 Halloween Party on October 30 during the recess. If you have any Halloween decoration stuff that you can support this event, please let any staff or myself know. Any new Halloween decoration ideas? Please share it with us.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month will start on Oct. 30 and end on Dec. 4. Please find attached form for your child/children\'s record. If you have any questions, please talk to your teacher.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Perfect Attendance</span></strong>\r\n\r\nMCS will continue award students with perfect attendance each semester. To be considered perfect attendance, absence per week <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">CAN NOT</span> be longer than 15 minutes.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Funding Raising</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Jitai &amp; Long-Hua Jhou (周治太, 駱龍華) picked up the bakery from QQ last week. We had an excellent bake sale and every thing was sold out within 15 mins. For those who came to parents lounge and didn\'t get any, we will have more next time.\r\n\r\nBake Sale: 3<sup>rd</sup> week on each month\r\n\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newsletter -10/23/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-10232010','','','2010-10-22 22:19:13','2010-10-23 02:19:13','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=100',0,'post','',0),(101,1,'2010-10-22 22:19:01','2010-10-23 02:19:01','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Lisa Hou\'s(侯珞怡) dedicated hard work to provide free teaching about <strong><strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (</strong></strong><strong><strong>注音符號</strong></strong><strong><strong>)</strong></strong> to MCS parents. School will send out survey to those adult students and if there is a need, we will consider offering a new tuition based adult CSL class.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Budget</span></strong>\n\nAfter parents meeting on 9/25/2010, some of you show the concern about our school budget not balanced from previous school year. There was a different between school account balance on 6/30/2010 and bank statement at that time. Jointed efforts was made by 2009-2010 Principal Tang (唐宗堯), current staff Jessica Lee (陳惠昭)and Chih-Wen Pai (白志文) and finally we have balanced the budget. When MCS started offering Ma Li-Ping classes back to several years ago, initially school purchased more teaching material than actually need in order to get the volume discount. At that time school counted it as an asset. Ideally, we will have to offset it when it was sold, but school counted it as an income. Therefore, there is a difference between school balance sheet and bank statement. We will have this issue corrected this year. We also will present this to parents Rep. during New Year Party preparation meeting (新年晚會籌備會議) scheduled on Nov.6. Everyone is welcomed to attend.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\n\nBased on our survey from each class, the majority prefer to have school wide Halloween Party as usual. We will have our 2010 Halloween Party on October 30 during the recess. If you have any Halloween decoration stuff that you can support this event, please let any staff or myself know. Any new Halloween decoration ideas? Please share it with us.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month will start on Oct. 30 and end on Dec. 4. Please find attached form for your child/children\'s record. If you have any questions, please talk to your teacher.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Perfect Attendance</span></strong>\n\nMCS will continue award students with perfect attendance each semester. To be considered perfect attendance, absence per week <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">CAN NOT</span> be longer than 15 minutes.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Funding Raising</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Jitai &amp; Long-Hua Jhou (周治太, 駱龍華) picked up the bakery from QQ last week. We had an excellent bake sale and every thing was sold out within 15 mins. For those who came to parents lounge and didn\'t get any, we will have more next time.\n\nBake Sale: 3<sup>rd</sup> week on each month\n\nJesse Wei\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newsletter -10/23/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','100-revision','','','2010-10-22 22:19:01','2010-10-23 02:19:01','',100,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=101',0,'revision','',0),(102,1,'2010-09-22 22:24:52','2010-09-23 02:24:52','<div><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; font-size: x-small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\"> </span></span>Happy Moon Festival !. First of all, I would like to thank 韓媽媽 baked the moon cake to our students and also provided the free moon cake for all teachers.</div>\r\n<div>(1)Fall Parents meeting 1:30 pm this Saturday at parents lounge. Please be there and we need your input.</div>\r\n<div>(2)<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>Home coming dress, shoes and accessory sale continue on this Saturday</em></span></strong></div>\r\n<div>(3)Free adult <strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (注音符號) </strong>class enrollment at parents lounge. Class starts on 10/2</div>\r\n<div>(4)Food service on Saturday 9/25: QQ 麵包, 雞腿便當, 肉圓 ,炒米粉 ,竽頭酥, 滷雞腿 ....等. Quantity is limited.</div>\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a></div>','NCS Newsletter - 9/25/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','92-revision-2','','','2010-09-22 22:24:52','2010-09-23 02:24:52','',92,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=102',0,'revision','',0),(103,1,'2010-10-28 12:19:21','2010-10-28 16:19:21','<div><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma; font-size: x-small;\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\"> </span></span>Happy Moon Festival !. First of all, I would like to thank 韓媽媽 baked the moon cake to our students and also provided the free moon cake for all teachers.</div>\r\n<div>(1)Fall Parents meeting 1:30 pm this Saturday at parents lounge. Please be there and we need your input.</div>\r\n<div>(2)<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>Home coming dress, shoes and accessory sale continue on this Saturday</em></span></strong></div>\r\n<div>(3)Free adult <strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (注音符號) </strong>class enrollment at parents lounge. Class starts on 10/2</div>\r\n<div>(4)Food service on Saturday 9/25: QQ 麵包, 雞腿便當, 肉圓 ,炒米粉 ,竽頭酥, 滷雞腿 ....等. Quantity is limited.</div>\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a></div>','MCS Newsletter - 9/25/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','92-revision-3','','','2010-10-28 12:19:21','2010-10-28 16:19:21','',92,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=103',0,'revision','',0),(104,1,'2010-10-28 12:22:22','2010-10-28 16:22:22','MCS Newsletter                                        Oct.30, 2010\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe will have our 2010 Halloween Parade on October 30 during the recess. All students are encouraged to wear their costumes to school. Just a reminder, no bloody make up, weapon or mask, because we have students at younger age. We will have parents lounge as event location and room will be closed from 1:00 pm till parade is over. Sorry for the inconvenient.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month will start on Oct. 30 and end on Dec. 4. Please find attached form for your child/children\'s record. If you have any questions, please talk to your teacher.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Funding Raising/Bake Sale</span></strong>\r\n\r\nLast week, kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) had free sample for her homemade 蜂蜜蛋糕. For those who had one or two or even more, you knew that\'s very delicious. Will inform you when she plans to have bake sale next time.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday (10/30) 黃勤珍(Chinchen Burkholder) will have 京餅, 豬肉餡餅, 芝麻甜餅. and Mrs. Xiao yu Shia  will have her homemade bake sale. Due to the Halloween Event, we will have this sale out side the parent lounge.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Lost and Found</span></strong>\r\n\r\nIf you left two Martha Stewart \"living\" magazine at parents lounge last week, please let me know.\r\n\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newletter -10/30/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newletter-10302010','','','2010-10-28 12:22:23','2010-10-28 16:22:23','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=104',0,'post','',0),(105,1,'2010-10-28 12:21:43','2010-10-28 16:21:43','MCS Newsletter                                        Oct.30, 2010\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\n\nWe will have our 2010 Halloween Parade on October 30 during the recess. All students are encouraged to wear their costumes to school. Just a reminder, no bloody make up, weapon or mask, because we have students at younger age. We will have parents lounge as event location and room will be closed from 1:00 pm till parade is over. Sorry for the inconvenient.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month will start on Oct. 30 and end on Dec. 4. Please find attached form for your child/children\'s record. If you have any questions, please talk to your teacher.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Funding Raising/Bake Sale</span></strong>\n\nLast week, kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) had free sample for her homemade 蜂蜜蛋糕. For those who had one or two or even more, you knew that\'s very delicious. Will inform you when she plans to have bake sale next time.\n\nThis Saturday (10/30) 黃勤珍(Chinchen Burkholder) will have 京餅, 豬肉餡餅, 芝麻甜餅. and Mrs. Xiao yu Shia  will have her homemade bake sale. Due to the Halloween Event, we will have this sale out side the parent lounge.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Lost and Found</span></strong>\n\nIf you left two Martha Stewart \"living\" magazine at parents lounge last week, please let me know.','MCS Newletter -10/30/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','104-revision','','','2010-10-28 12:21:43','2010-10-28 16:21:43','',104,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=105',0,'revision','',0),(106,1,'2010-11-05 22:02:42','2010-11-06 02:02:42','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to kindergarten parent林曉君(Vicky) fund raising. She had her bake sale last week and donated all money to school.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to all staff and parents, we had a wonderful Halloween party.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Did you know all the bats in different size on window blinds were hand made by 陳俐君(Tracy Wu) ?</li>\r\n	<li>Did you notice some pumpkins were smoking? That\'s special dry ice effect provided by   呂思平(Szuping Lu).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlso we had many hand carved pumpkins on display.\r\n\r\nWe spent a little, but enjoyed A LOT. The event expense meets our budget. Once again, thanks to staff and parents who helped to decorate the parent lounge and clean up at the end. Also thanks to staff and parents who stood in the aisle to distribute candy to students and this event can\'t be succeeded without your support.\r\n\r\nAll event pictures are available on school website under \"Album\" or follow the link below.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/MichiganChineseSchool/Halloween2010\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/MichiganChineseSchool/Halloween2010</a>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBecause we want to hear from you about the teaching environment/style for your child/children, we will have teachers survey soon. Each parent rep. will hand out a hard copy of survey form to each parent. Please sit down with your child, go over the form and fill it out. We believe there is always room for improvement and would like to have proper communication channel between parents/students and teacher.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Parents Rep. /Staff Meeting</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis Saturday (11/6), all staff and parent rep. from each class are invited to attend.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Location: Parents Lounge Room 2423/2425</li>\r\n	<li>Meeting Start Time: 1:40 pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\r\n\r\n波霸奶茶- provided by kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky). All sale will 100% donate to school.','MCS Newsletter Nov.6, 2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-nov-6-2010','','','2010-11-05 22:02:42','2010-11-06 02:02:42','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=106',0,'post','',0),(107,1,'2010-11-05 22:01:55','2010-11-06 02:01:55','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to kindergarten parent林曉君(Vicky) fund raising. She had her bake sale last week and donated all money to school.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\n\nThanks to all staff and parents, we had a wonderful Halloween party.\n<ul>\n	<li>Did you know all the bats in different size on window blinds were hand made by 陳俐君(Tracy Wu) ?</li>\n	<li>Did you notice some pumpkins were smoking? That\'s special dry ice effect provided by   呂思平(Szuping Lu).</li>\n</ul>\nAlso we had many hand carved pumpkins on display.\n\nWe spent a little, but enjoyed A LOT. The event expense meets our budget. Once again, thanks to staff and parents who helped to decorate the parent lounge and clean up at the end. Also thanks to staff and parents who stood in the aisle to distribute candy to students and this event can\'t be succeeded without your support.\n\nAll event pictures are available on school website under \"Album\" or follow the link below.\n\n<a href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/MichiganChineseSchool/Halloween2010\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/MichiganChineseSchool/Halloween2010</a>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\n\nBecause we want to hear from you about the teaching environment/style for your child/children, we will have teachers survey soon. Each parent rep. will hand out a hard copy of survey form to each parent. Please sit down with your child, go over the form and fill it out. We believe there is always room for improvement and would like to have proper communication channel between parents/students and teacher.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Parents Rep. /Staff Meeting</span></strong>\n\nThis Saturday (11/6), all staff and parent rep. from each class are invited to attend.\n<ul>\n	<li>Location: Parents Lounge Room 2423/2425</li>\n	<li>Meeting Start Time: 1:40 pm</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\n\n波霸奶茶- provided by kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky). All sale will 100% donate to school.','MCS Newsletter Nov.6, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','106-revision','','','2010-11-05 22:01:55','2010-11-06 02:01:55','',106,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=107',0,'revision','',0),(108,1,'2010-11-12 00:20:19','2010-11-12 04:20:19','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Thanks to 唐宗堯, 張子若 (Alex and Joanne Tang) donation to Michigan Chinese School.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Thanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) fund raising. She had波霸奶茶 sale last week and donated all money to school.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThe survey forms had been given to parent rep. last Saturday and all parents should receive one. If you don\'t have it, make sure contact your parent rep. Please sit down with your child, go over the survey and fill it out. Please return the completed survey no later than 11/20 to your parent rep. This is an anonymous survey, but you need to list the class/grade.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 New Year Party Preparation Meeting</span></strong>\r\n\r\nMeeting was held last week. Below is brief summary:\r\n\r\nLocation: Stevenson High School\r\n\r\nTime:  2:30 – 8:00 pm\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 Directory</span></strong>\r\n\r\nDirectory is completed and will be available this Saturday. Please stop by Parents Lounge during regular school hour to pick up.\r\n\r\nHunan Hunan will be on campus this Saturday.',' MCS Newsletter         Nov.13, 20',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-nov-13-20','','','2010-11-12 00:20:19','2010-11-12 04:20:19','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=108',0,'post','',0),(109,1,'2010-11-12 00:19:46','2010-11-12 04:19:46','',' MCS Newsletter         Nov.13, 20',0,'','inherit','open','open','','108-revision','','','2010-11-12 00:19:46','2010-11-12 04:19:46','',108,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=109',0,'revision','',0),(110,1,'2010-11-19 08:47:37','2010-11-19 12:47:37','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) fund raising last week.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe want to hear your voice by anonymous survey. If you don\'t have survey form, make sure to contact your parent rep. Please sit down with your child, go over the survey and fill it out. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Return the completed survey no later than 11/20 to your parent rep. </span>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 Directory</span></strong>\r\n\r\nDirectory is ready and available to pick up during regular school hour at parents lounge. Thanks to賴昭宇 (Jauyeu Lai) hard work to make school directory in time for delivery. Do you notice we have very good quality on directory paper and a transparent cover? Higher quality, but lower expense.\r\n\r\nIf you are going to have business with those advertisement sponsors on our directory, Please mention you saw their advertisement on Michigan Chinese School directory and thanks their support.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>QQ bakery this week. Due to popular demand, we have increase our bakery order from last time. Hope everyone can enjoy and support this event.</li>\r\n	<li>Walnut pumpkin pie by 林曉君(Vicky) – limited quantity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Thanksgiving</span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Soon Thanksgiving will become the focus of our attention. The upcoming seasons allow us to celebrate the most valuable gifts we have been given---those of love, family, friends, health, peace, and the opportunity to give thanks and to share our gifts with one another.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>There will be no school on Nov. 27. </strong></li>\r\n</ul>','MCS Newsletter    Nov.20, 2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-nov-20-2010','','','2010-11-19 08:47:37','2010-11-19 12:47:37','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=110',0,'post','',0),(111,1,'2010-11-19 08:47:35','2010-11-19 12:47:35','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) fund raising last week.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\n\nWe want to hear your voice by anonymous survey. If you don\'t have survey form, make sure to contact your parent rep. Please sit down with your child, go over the survey and fill it out. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Return the completed survey no later than 11/20 to your parent rep. </span>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 Directory</span></strong>\n\nDirectory is ready and available to pick up during regular school hour at parents lounge. Thanks to賴昭宇 (Jauyeu Lai) hard work to make school directory in time for delivery. Do you notice we have very good quality on directory paper and a transparent cover? Higher quality, but lower expense.\n\nIf you are going to have business with those advertisement sponsors on our directory, Please mention you saw their advertisement on Michigan Chinese School directory and thanks their support.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>QQ bakery this week. Due to popular demand, we have increase our bakery order from last time. Hope everyone can enjoy and support this event.</li>\n	<li>Walnut pumpkin pie by 林曉君(Vicky) – limited quantity</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Thanksgiving</span></strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Soon Thanksgiving will become the focus of our attention. The upcoming seasons allow us to celebrate the most valuable gifts we have been given---those of love, family, friends, health, peace, and the opportunity to give thanks and to share our gifts with one another.</li>\n	<li><strong>There will be no school on Nov. 27. </strong></li>\n</ul>','MCS Newsletter    Nov.20, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','110-revision','','','2010-11-19 08:47:35','2010-11-19 12:47:35','',110,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=111',0,'revision','',0),(112,1,'2010-12-02 22:54:09','2010-12-03 02:54:09','MCS Newsletter                                        Dec. 4, 2010\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky)  pumpkin pies fund raising on Nov.20. Vicky has been running her bake  sale and donated all money to school for last four weeks.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe are collecting the survey from all classes and will review the result with each teacher individually.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month will be ended on Dec. 4. Please have student turn in his/her recording form to teacher this Saturday. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Late submission will not be accepted</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Special Presentation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nPresenter: Joel Levi\r\n\r\nSubject: Pre-paid Legal Service\r\n\r\nDate: 12/4/2010\r\n\r\nTime: 1:45 PM\r\n\r\nLocation: Parents Lounge\r\n\r\nThe  presenter put an ad in our directory to support our school (see  attached).  Pre-paid Legal Service is a very new idea, kind of like  buying insurance for the legal services that we might need down the  road. We encourage parents to come to learn something new and also  support our advertiser.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">全球華文網」新闢「學生華語創作園地」</span></strong>\r\n\r\n為使全球華語文相關工作者及教師能分享華文教學經驗及心情故事，僑委會於本（99）年4月起辦理「全球華文網」之「我的華文故事」徵文活動，業獲致良好迴響。茲為使華語文學習者亦有發表作品及分享學習心得之場域，特自本年11月起在「我的華文故事」專區增闢「學生華語創作園地」專欄。鼓勵學子們踴躍投稿，前揭專欄網址請由「全球華文網」（<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.huayuworld.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.huayuworld.org</a>）首頁「我的華文故事」項下進入。\r\n\r\n相關聯結網址：<a href=\"http://www.huayuworld.org/?p=9760\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.huayuworld.org/?p=9760</a>','MCS Newsletter -12/4/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-1242010','','','2010-12-02 22:54:09','2010-12-03 02:54:09','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=112',0,'post','',0),(113,1,'2010-12-02 22:53:58','2010-12-03 02:53:58','MCS Newsletter                                        Dec. 4, 2010\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky)  pumpkin pies fund raising on Nov.20. Vicky has been running her bake  sale and donated all money to school for last four weeks.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\n\nWe are collecting the survey from all classes and will review the result with each teacher individually.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month will be ended on Dec. 4. Please have student turn in his/her recording form to teacher this Saturday. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Late submission will not be accepted</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">.</span>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\n</span>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Special Presentation</span></strong>\n\nPresenter: Joel Levi\n\nSubject: Pre-paid Legal Service\n\nDate: 12/4/2010\n\nTime: 1:45 PM\n\nLocation: Parents Lounge\n\nThe  presenter put an ad in our directory to support our school (see  attached).  Pre-paid Legal Service is a very new idea, kind of like  buying insurance for the legal services that we might need down the  road. We encourage parents to come to learn something new and also  support our advertiser.\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">全球華文網」新闢「學生華語創作園地」</span></strong>\n\n為使全球華語文相關工作者及教師能分享華文教學經驗及心情故事，僑委會於本（99）年4月起辦理「全球華文網」之「我的華文故事」徵文活動，業獲致良好迴響。茲為使華語文學習者亦有發表作品及分享學習心得之場域，特自本年11月起在「我的華文故事」專區增闢「學生華語創作園地」專欄。鼓勵學子們踴躍投稿，前揭專欄網址請由「全球華文網」（<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.huayuworld.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.huayuworld.org</a>）首頁「我的華文故事」項下進入。\n\n相關聯結網址：<a href=\"http://www.huayuworld.org/?p=9760\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.huayuworld.org/?p=9760</a>','MCS Newsletter -12/4/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','112-revision','','','2010-12-02 22:53:58','2010-12-03 02:53:58','',112,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=113',0,'revision','',0),(114,1,'2010-12-10 22:25:55','2010-12-11 02:25:55','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Jitai &amp; Long-Hua Jhou (周治太, 駱龍華) picked up the bakery from QQ on Nov.20.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAward will be presented this week to each student who read more than 240 mins during reading month.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Special Presentation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had a presentation about \"Pre-paid Legal Service\" last week and anyone who is interested can visit their website: <a title=\"blocked::http://www.prepaidlegal.com/hub/phasefour\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.prepaidlegal.com/hub/phasefour\" target=\"_blank\">www.prepaidlegal.com/hub/phasefour</a> and/or call direct at (877) 251-9472.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan  will be on campus this Saturday. You can order in advanced and pick up  at school hours. See contact information in 2010-2011 school directory  page A-9.','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 11, 2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-dec-11-2010','','','2010-12-10 22:25:55','2010-12-11 02:25:55','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=114',0,'post','',0),(115,1,'2010-12-10 22:25:13','2010-12-11 02:25:13','','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 11, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','114-revision','','','2010-12-10 22:25:13','2010-12-11 02:25:13','',114,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=115',0,'revision','',0),(116,1,'2010-12-16 18:10:45','2010-12-16 22:10:45','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Szuping Lu\'s(呂思平) dedicated hard work. With his family support, we have very creative and unique reading month award this year.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Job Opportunity</span></strong>\r\n\r\nFord Powertrain Manufacturing Engineering has following jobs opening.\r\n\r\n1. Machining\r\n\r\n●Gears   ●Aluminum Machining   ●Tooling   ●Gauging\r\n\r\n2. Metallurgy\r\n\r\n3. Industrial / Plant Engineer\r\n\r\n●Industrial Engineer   ●Plant Layout   ●Material Handling\r\n\r\n4. Assembly and Test Engineer\r\n\r\nIf  you or you know of any talented people out there looking for work,  please direct them to the website to complete a career profile.\r\n\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://corporate.ford.com/careers/north-american-careers/job-openings\" target=\"_blank\">http://corporate.ford.com/careers/north-american-careers/job-openings</a>:\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  have collected surveys from all classes and will review result with  each teacher individually to ensure the communication between teachers  and parents/students.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\r\n\r\nQQ bakery this week.  Please remember 3<sup>rd</sup> week each month, we will have QQ bakery sale as our fund raising.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Your Support Makes All The Difference</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBecause  of support received from you and other generous individuals, we have  been able to make real progress toward furthering our important mission.\r\n\r\nFor upcoming year, there are several major events:\r\n\r\n(1)   January – 新年晚會\r\n\r\n(2)   April - 校內演講比賽\r\n\r\n<strong>(3) </strong>May -校際演講比賽 – <strong>將由本校負責主辦</strong>\r\n\r\n(4)   June - 認字比賽\r\n\r\n(5)   June - 畢業典禮\r\n\r\nBecause  of people like you, our vision and mission are possible. We truly  appreciate your thoughtfulness and want you to know that no matter how  much you choose to give, you are making a big difference for our school.  A bonus is that your gift may also qualify for a tax break for 2010  when you itemize deductions on your federal income tax return. We\'ll  issue a tax receipt to you for your contribution and also announce in  our weekly newsletter.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">元旦升旗典禮</span></strong>\r\n\r\n因響應全球同步升旗慶祝中華民國一百周年的第一天,密西根僑民將於元月一日上午十一點,在美華中心廣場舉行密西根的升旗典禮(全球以美國加州時間早上八點為準),希望台灣僑民們踴躍參加,也歡迎攜帶美國當地朋友參加,升旗典禮過後,於12點籌備會將提供多種粥點,以祛寒氣,希望僑學各界能多多呼朋引友踴躍參加,也希望鼓勵年輕學子參與.\r\n\r\n時間 : 元月一日上午十一點,\r\n\r\n地點 : 美華活動中心廣場:32585 Concord Drive, Madison Hts., MI 48071\r\n\r\n有問題者可洽: 周綵玲2483208888孫絡典5868263936\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Holidays Break</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThere will be no school for 12/25/2010 and 1/1/2011, due to holidays break. We  wish your family the gifts of joy, good health and peace this  season. We wish you warm wonderful times with family and friends and  much love. We look forward to exciting and challenging new learning  experiences in the 2011 New Year!','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 18, 2010',0,'','publish','open','open','','mcs-newsletter-dec-18-2010','','','2010-12-16 18:10:45','2010-12-16 22:10:45','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=116',0,'post','',0),(117,1,'2010-12-16 18:10:06','2010-12-16 22:10:06','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Szuping Lu\'s(呂思平) dedicated hard work. With his family support, we have very creative and unique reading month award this year.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Job Opportunity</span></strong>\n\nFord Powertrain Manufacturing Engineering has following jobs opening.\n\n1. Machining\n\n●Gears   ●Aluminum Machining   ●Tooling   ●Gauging\n\n2. Metallurgy\n\n3. Industrial / Plant Engineer\n\n●Industrial Engineer   ●Plant Layout   ●Material Handling\n\n4. Assembly and Test Engineer\n\nIf  you or you know of any talented people out there looking for work,  please direct them to the website to complete a career profile.\n\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://corporate.ford.com/careers/north-american-careers/job-openings\" target=\"_blank\">http://corporate.ford.com/careers/north-american-careers/job-openings</a>:\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\n\nWe  have collected surveys from all classes and will review result with  each teacher individually to ensure the communication between teachers  and parents/students.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\n\nQQ bakery this week.  Please remember 3<sup>rd</sup> week each month, we will have QQ bakery sale as our fund raising.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Your Support Makes All The Difference</span></strong>\n\nBecause  of support received from you and other generous individuals, we have  been able to make real progress toward furthering our important mission.\n\nFor upcoming year, there are several major events:\n\n(1)   January – 新年晚會\n\n(2)   April - 校內演講比賽\n\n<strong>(3) </strong>May -校際演講比賽 – <strong>將由本校負責主辦</strong>\n\n(4)   June - 認字比賽\n\n(5)   June - 畢業典禮\n\nBecause  of people like you, our vision and mission are possible. We truly  appreciate your thoughtfulness and want you to know that no matter how  much you choose to give, you are making a big difference for our school.  A bonus is that your gift may also qualify for a tax break for 2010  when you itemize deductions on your federal income tax return. We\'ll  issue a tax receipt to you for your contribution and also announce in  our weekly newsletter.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">元旦升旗典禮</span></strong>\n\n因響應全球同步升旗慶祝中華民國一百周年的第一天,密西根僑民將於元月一日上午十一點,在美華中心廣場舉行密西根的升旗典禮(全球以美國加州時間早上八點為準),希望台灣僑民們踴躍參加,也歡迎攜帶美國當地朋友參加,升旗典禮過後,於12點籌備會將提供多種粥點,以祛寒氣,希望僑學各界能多多呼朋引友踴躍參加,也希望鼓勵年輕學子參與.\n\n時間 : 元月一日上午十一點,\n\n地點 : 美華活動中心廣場:32585 Concord Drive, Madison Hts., MI 48071\n\n有問題者可洽: 周綵玲2483208888孫絡典5868263936\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Holidays Break</span></strong>\n\nThere will be no school for 12/25/2010 and 1/1/2011, due to holidays break. We  wish your family the gifts of joy, good health and peace this  season. We wish you warm wonderful times with family and friends and  much love. We look forward to exciting and challenging new learning  experiences in the 2011 New Year!','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 18, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','116-revision','','','2010-12-16 18:10:06','2010-12-16 22:10:06','',116,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=117',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2011-01-08 00:23:08','2011-01-08 04:23:08','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Happy New Year</span></strong>\r\n\r\nI hope all of you enjoyed the holiday break and spent some relaxing time with friends and family.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Communication</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAs  we discussed at beginning of school year, we would like to promote  email communication between teachers and parents/students so that we can  save paper and protect environment. Teachers will send out weekly  teaching progress and homework assignment by email. If you don’t have  computer to access these communication, you can stop by Madonna  University library during our regular school hours and there are many  computers available.\r\n\r\nWhile  I organized our school contact directory, I noticed that several  families were not on the weekly newsletter distribution list. If you  didn\'t receive our weekly newsletters in the past, you can go to school  website for archive information.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  had reviewed the survey result with each teacher individually on  12/18/2010. This survey served as a bridge between teachers and  parents/students and we will conduct another survey on later part of  this school year.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Pre-Register for 2<sup>nd</sup> semester </span></strong>\r\n\r\nPre-register  for next semester will begin this week (1/8) and end on (1/15). You can  save $20.00 for each student, if you pre-register. It\'s school policy  that if you do not pre-register, <strong><em>you will be charged $20.00 registration fee for each student you enroll.</em></strong><strong> </strong>Registration form is attached and also available on school website.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEvent Date: Saturday, 1/29/2011\r\n\r\nTickets on sale: 1/8/2011. Adults: $10.00, Students: $5.00\r\n\r\nNew Year Party is <strong><em>one </em></strong>event includes students\' performance and dinner.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Calendars</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  will have some 2011 calendars from Taiwan available this Saturday at  parents lounge. Limited quantity and first come first serve.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter        Jan. 8, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-jan-8-2011','','','2011-01-08 00:23:08','2011-01-08 04:23:08','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=118',0,'post','',0),(119,1,'2011-01-08 00:22:43','2011-01-08 04:22:43','','MCS Newsletter        Jan. 8, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','118-revision','','','2011-01-08 00:22:43','2011-01-08 04:22:43','',118,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=119',0,'revision','',0),(120,1,'2011-01-20 00:10:38','2011-01-20 04:10:38','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kevin Wang (王惠章) picking up the bakery from QQ bakery last week.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spring 2010-2011</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis  weekend will be the beginning of Spring 2010-2011 semester. Welcome  those new students and families. Because New Year Party is scheduled  next week, <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">we will have after school curriculums this week for those who need more practice.</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEvent Date: Saturday, 1/29/2011 at 2:30 pm\r\n\r\nTickets on sale now: Adults: $10.00, Students: $5.00\r\n\r\nNew Year Party is <strong><em>one </em></strong>event includes students\' performance and dinner.\r\n\r\nWe are highly encouraging all school members to invite friends and families to celebrate the year of rabbit.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party Last Preparation Meeting</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe will have one more meeting for all parents rep\'s from each class and staff this week to make sure we have everything covered.\r\n\r\nLocation: Parents Lounge\r\n\r\nTime: 1:45pm','MCS Newsletter  Jan. 22, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-jan-22-2011','','','2011-01-20 00:10:38','2011-01-20 04:10:38','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=120',0,'post','',0),(121,1,'2011-01-20 00:10:05','2011-01-20 04:10:05','','MCS Newsletter  ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','120-revision','','','2011-01-20 00:10:05','2011-01-20 04:10:05','',120,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=121',0,'revision','',0),(122,1,'2011-02-03 21:27:54','2011-02-04 01:27:54','<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Rose Geist (尹新妹) generous donation to Michigan Chinese School.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had a very successful New Year Party on Jan.29 at Stevenson High School. Thanks to all teachers and students\' hard work to practice their entertainment program. Also thanks to all staff and parents who spent so much efforts and time on this event. Without your support, we won\'t have this annual event.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures/DVD</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had two photographers Hank Kwong (鄺力衡) and Sylvia Richards (劉蔚芝) taking pictures in this event. Hank had all his photos ready in the following link and Sylvia will have her photos ready soon. We will also have links add to school website for your viewing purpose. Feel free to download the pictures you like and thanks to them when you meet them next time.\r\n\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email</a>\r\n\r\nIf you want to purchase a copy of New Year Party DVD, please sign in this Saturday at Parent\'s Lounge. $5.00 only.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">張奶奶壓歲錢</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis will be distributed during class this Saturday. Students/Parents don\'t forget to thank 張奶奶\r\n\r\nnext time when you see her.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Academic Excellent Award</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom. Only for classes that teacher provided the list.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Spring After School Curriculum Registration</span></strong>\r\n\r\nRegistration will begin this week.','MCS Newsletter    Feb.5, 2011 ',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-feb-5-2011','','','2011-02-03 21:27:54','2011-02-04 01:27:54','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=122',0,'post','',0),(123,1,'2011-02-03 21:27:41','2011-02-04 01:27:41','<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Rose Geist (尹新妹) generous donation to Michigan Chinese School.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party</span></strong>\n\nWe had a very successful New Year Party on Jan.29 at Stevenson High School. Thanks to all teachers and students\' hard work to practice their entertainment program. Also thanks to all staff and parents who spent so much efforts and time on this event. Without your support, we won\'t have this annual event.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures/DVD</span></strong>\n\nWe had two photographers Hank Kwong (鄺力衡) and Sylvia Richards (劉蔚芝) taking pictures in this event. Hank had all his photos ready in the following link and Sylvia will have her photos ready soon. We will also have links add to school website for your viewing purpose. Feel free to download the pictures you like and thanks to them when you meet them next time.\n\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email</a>\n\nIf you want to purchase a copy of New Year Party DVD, please sign in this Saturday at Parent\'s Lounge. $5.00 only.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">張奶奶壓歲錢</span></strong>\n\nThis will be distributed during class this Saturday. Students/Parents don\'t forget to thank 張奶奶\n\nnext time when you see her.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Academic Excellent Award</span></strong>\n\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom. Only for classes that teacher provided the list.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Spring After School Curriculum Registration</span></strong>\n\nRegistration will begin this week.','MCS Newsletter    Feb.5, 2011 ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','122-revision','','','2011-02-03 21:27:41','2011-02-04 01:27:41','',122,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=123',0,'revision','',0),(124,1,'2011-02-09 21:30:59','2011-02-10 01:30:59','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures from Sylvia Richards (</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">劉蔚芝</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">)</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Sylvia providing the following link to view all pictures she took on 1/29.\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://picasaweb.google.com/snap2shot/20110129MCSChineseNewYearParty?authkey=Gv1sRgCM3MjLexmb6b4wE&amp;feat=directlink\" target=\"_blank\">https://picasaweb.google.com/snap2shot/20110129MCSChineseNewYearParty?authkey=Gv1sRgCM3MjLexmb6b4wE&amp;feat=directlink</a>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Video</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEntire program DVD is available for you to own with cost of $5.00.  Sing up sheet is in parents lounge.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Perfect Attendance Award</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Movie </span></strong>\r\n\r\nStudents (鄺紹耘, 王淨德, 王淨慧, 邱晧)  from our school took part in the movie Smooch.  It will be showing on  Hallmark channel on 2/11 at 9:00 pm and 2/12 at 3:00 pm.\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter          Feb.12, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-feb-12-2011','','','2011-02-09 21:30:59','2011-02-10 01:30:59','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=124',0,'post','',0),(125,1,'2011-02-09 21:30:46','2011-02-10 01:30:46','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures from Sylvia Richards (</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">劉蔚芝</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">)</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Sylvia providing the following link to view all pictures she took on 1/29.\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://picasaweb.google.com/snap2shot/20110129MCSChineseNewYearParty?authkey=Gv1sRgCM3MjLexmb6b4wE&amp;feat=directlink\" target=\"_blank\">https://picasaweb.google.com/snap2shot/20110129MCSChineseNewYearParty?authkey=Gv1sRgCM3MjLexmb6b4wE&amp;feat=directlink</a>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Video</span></strong>\n\nEntire program DVD is available for you to own with cost of $5.00.  Sing up sheet is in parents lounge.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Perfect Attendance Award</span></strong>\n\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Movie </span></strong>\n\nStudents (鄺紹耘, 王淨德, 王淨慧, 邱晧)  from our school took part in the movie Smooch.  It will be showing on  Hallmark channel on 2/11 at 9:00 pm and 2/12 at 3:00 pm.\n\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter          Feb.12, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','124-revision','','','2011-02-09 21:30:46','2011-02-10 01:30:46','',124,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=125',0,'revision','',0),(126,1,'2011-02-16 14:15:29','2011-02-16 18:15:29','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Vicky Lin (林曉君) Valentine\'s sweet sale last week and all sales donated to school.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Message from Madonna University </span></strong>\r\n\r\nMadonna University  reported there was equipment damage recently in one of our classrooms.  It\'s hard to believe this was conducted by our students/teachers unless  they can provide evidence. But I would like to emphasize and remind you  the following:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>All  equipment in each classroom is for teaching purpose. It\'s not a toy,  nor game. Madonna University provides us an excellent learning  environment.</li>\r\n	<li>Students <strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">shouldn\'t</span></em></strong> play with in classroom equipment unless it is under teacher\'s supervision and for study purpose only.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents,  please communicate with your child/children that don\'t stay in  classroom or play with computer equipment after regular school hour.</li>\r\n	<li>At the end of class, please return everything back to its original location. You moved it and you put it back.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Video/DVD</span></strong>\r\n\r\nFor those who signed up to purchase 2011 New Year Party DVD, please come to parents lounge at first hour to pick up your DVD. The cost is $5.00. Thanks to Jauyeu Lai (賴昭宇) spent a lot of personal time to make this happen.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Website </span></strong>\r\n\r\nHave you visited our school website lately? <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\r\n\r\nThanks to Steven Lien who updated the pictures and 2011 New Year Party pictures links.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising </span></strong>\r\n\r\nIt\'s 3<sup>rd</sup> Saturday again. As usual, we will have QQ bakery as our school fund raising. Don\'t miss it and be there in time.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Winter Break </span></strong>\r\n\r\nThere will be no school next Saturday (2/26/2011), due to winter break. Wish ever family has a relaxed and safe break.','MCS Newsletter     Feb.19, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-feb-19-2011','','','2011-02-16 14:15:29','2011-02-16 18:15:29','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=126',0,'post','',0),(127,1,'2011-02-16 14:14:45','2011-02-16 18:14:45','','MCS Newsletter     Feb.19, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','126-revision','','','2011-02-16 14:14:45','2011-02-16 18:14:45','',126,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=127',0,'revision','',0),(128,1,'2011-03-02 20:35:15','2011-03-03 00:35:15','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kevin Wang (王惠章) picking up QQ bakery last time and made our fund raising successful.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\r\n\r\nMCS speech contest is scheduled on 4/9 and registration is begun. Parents please encourage your child/children to participate and help them to practice. If any parents need extra support, please talk to your teacher first. If additional support is needed, please contact Mei-Ying Huang (教務主任- 黃玫瑛).\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Promotion </span></strong>\r\n\r\nOne of our 2010-2011 directory sponsors – hair stylist Ms. Noel Leung will be at parents lounge this Saturday with fliers from her hair salon.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 School Directory Amendment</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe have several new families jointed us this semester and attached is the directory supplemental.\r\n\r\nChinChen Burkholder (黃勤珍) will have bakery for sales this week at parents lounge.','MCS Newsletter  March 5, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-march-5-2011','','','2011-03-02 20:35:51','2011-03-03 00:35:51','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=128',0,'post','',0),(129,1,'2011-03-02 20:34:55','2011-03-03 00:34:55','','MCS Newsletter  March 5, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','128-revision','','','2011-03-02 20:34:55','2011-03-03 00:34:55','',128,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=129',0,'revision','',0),(130,1,'2011-03-02 20:35:15','2011-03-03 00:35:15','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kevin Wang (王惠章) picking up QQ bakery last time and made our fund raising successful.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\r\n\r\nMCS speech contest is scheduled on 4/9 and registration is begun. Parents please encourage your child/children to participate and help them to practice. If any parents need extra support, please talk to your teacher first. If additional support is needed, please contact Mei-Ying Huang (教務主任- 黃玫瑛).\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Promotion </span></strong>\r\n\r\nOne of our 2010-2011 directory sponsors – hair stylist Ms. Noel Leung will be at parents lounge this Saturday with fliers from her hair salon.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 School Directory Amendment</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe have several new families jointed us this semester and attached is the directory supplemental.\r\n\r\nChinChen Burkholder (黃勤珍) will have bakery for sales this week at parents lounge.','MCS Newsletter  March 5, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','128-revision-2','','','2011-03-02 20:35:15','2011-03-03 00:35:15','',128,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=130',0,'revision','',0),(131,1,'2011-03-09 19:30:51','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','MCS NewsletterMarch 12, 2011',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2011-03-09 19:30:51','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=131',0,'post','',0),(132,1,'2011-03-09 19:30:56','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to馬文豪,王南鳳(Wen-Hou &amp; Nan-Fong Ma) donating their referral fee to school.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\n\nMCS  speech contest is scheduled on 4/9 and registration deadline is this  Saturday (3/12). Parents please encourage your child/children to  participate either speech or看圖說故事比賽.  If any parents need extra support, please talk to your teacher first.  If additional support is needed, please contact Mei-Ying Huang (教務主任- 黃玫瑛).\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">SATII Mock Test </span></strong>\n\nSeveral  students signed up to take the SAT this Saturday. Please have your  students report to Room 2421 (next to parents lounge) at 1:30pm.  Bring  with them No. 2 pencils and eraser.\nWe will provide drink and snack.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Presentation – Preparing for College (next week) </span></strong>\n\nWe are glad to have Kelley Wu (吳可琳) Admission Advisor at Eastern Michigan University\n\n(2004 密西根中文學校畢業)  come to our school next week (3/19). The presentation will be based on  Admission adviser view point on how to prepare for college. She will  give a presentation and after that open the floor for questions. Please  invite anyone who may be interested in this topic.\n\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter     March 12, 2011',0,'','draft','closed','open','','','','','2011-03-09 19:30:56','2011-03-09 23:30:56','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=132',0,'post','',0),(133,1,'2011-03-09 19:31:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to馬文豪,王南鳳(Wen-Hou &amp; Nan-Fong Ma) donating their referral fee to school.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\n\nMCS  speech contest is scheduled on 4/9 and registration deadline is this  Saturday (3/12). Parents please encourage your child/children to  participate either speech or看圖說故事比賽.  If any parents need extra support, please talk to your teacher first.  If additional support is needed, please contact Mei-Ying Huang (教務主任- 黃玫瑛).\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">SATII Mock Test </span></strong>\n\nSeveral  students signed up to take the SAT this Saturday. Please have your  students report to Room 2421 (next to parents lounge) at 1:30pm.  Bring  with them No. 2 pencils and eraser.\nWe will provide drink and snack.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Presentation – Preparing for College (next week) </span></strong>\n\nWe are glad to have Kelley Wu (吳可琳) Admission Advisor at Eastern Michigan University\n\n(2004 密西根中文學校畢業)  come to our school next week (3/19). The presentation will be based on  Admission adviser view point on how to prepare for college. She will  give a presentation and after that open the floor for questions. Please  invite anyone who may be interested in this topic.\n\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter - 3/12/2011',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2011-03-09 19:31:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=133',0,'post','',0),(134,1,'2011-03-09 19:32:45','2011-03-09 23:32:45','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to馬文豪,王南鳳(Wen-Hou &amp; Nan-Fong Ma) donating their referral fee to school.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\r\n\r\nMCS  speech contest is scheduled on 4/9 and registration deadline is this  Saturday (3/12). Parents please encourage your child/children to  participate either speech or看圖說故事比賽.  If any parents need extra support, please talk to your teacher first.  If additional support is needed, please contact Mei-Ying Huang (教務主任- 黃玫瑛).\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">SATII Mock Test </span></strong>\r\n\r\nSeveral  students signed up to take the SAT this Saturday. Please have your  students report to Room 2421 (next to parents lounge) at 1:30pm.  Bring  with them No. 2 pencils and eraser.\r\nWe will provide drink and snack.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Presentation – Preparing for College (next week) </span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe are glad to have Kelley Wu (吳可琳) Admission Advisor at Eastern Michigan University\r\n\r\n(2004 密西根中文學校畢業)  come to our school next week (3/19). The presentation will be based on  Admission adviser view point on how to prepare for college. She will  give a presentation and after that open the floor for questions. Please  invite anyone who may be interested in this topic.\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter - 3/12/2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-3122011','','','2011-03-09 19:32:45','2011-03-09 23:32:45','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=134',0,'post','',0),(135,1,'2011-03-09 19:32:28','2011-03-09 23:32:28','','MCS Newsletter - 3/12/2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','134-revision','','','2011-03-09 19:32:28','2011-03-09 23:32:28','',134,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=135',0,'revision','',0),(136,1,'2011-03-16 20:44:00','2011-03-17 00:44:00','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to賴哲琛, 劉怡均(Allen Lai &amp; Julia Liu) donating their referral fee to school. Also\r\n\r\nThanks to 陳俐君 (Tracy Wu) donating her cupcakes sales last week to school.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Presentation – Preparing for College </span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe are glad to have Kelley Wu (吳可琳) Admission Advisor at Eastern Michigan University\r\n\r\n(2004 密西根中文學校畢業)  come to our school this week (3/19) to have a presentation for all  parents and G-10 students. The presentation will be based on Admission  adviser view point on how to prepare for college. She will give a  presentation and after that open the floor for questions. Please invite  anyone who may be interested in this topic. Presentation starts at 1:45  pm. at Parents Lounge.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\r\n\r\nPlease mark your calendar, MCS speech contest is scheduled on Saturday 4/9/2011.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising </span></strong>\r\n\r\nAs usual, we will have QQ bakery as our school fund raising this Saturday. Don\'t miss it and be there in time.','MCS Newsletter - 3/19/2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-3192011','','','2011-03-16 20:44:00','2011-03-17 00:44:00','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=136',0,'post','',0),(137,1,'2011-03-16 20:43:26','2011-03-17 00:43:26','','MCS Newsletter - 3/19/2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','136-revision','','','2011-03-16 20:43:26','2011-03-17 00:43:26','',136,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=137',0,'revision','',0),(138,1,'2011-03-23 23:31:38','2011-03-24 03:31:38','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kelley Wu (吳可琳)  \"Planning for College\" presentation last week. We had G-10 students and  parents attend this presentation. Many questions were discussed during  this one hour presentation. We also want to thanks Shee-Tak Loh (陸樹德) who spent time to make this event happened.\r\n\r\nYou can find completed presentation material in our school Website.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">QQ Bakery on Break </span></strong>\r\n\r\nMany  of you were disappointed when founded out there was no QQ bakery fund  raising last week. This is because the owner of QQ bakery is on vacation  and store is closed for three weeks. We didn\'t know this till last  Friday.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\r\n\r\nPlease  mark your calendar, MCS speech contest is scheduled on Saturday  4/9/2011. The top three place students will have the chance to attend  Interschool Speech Contest on 5/7/2011 which is hosted by our school.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">健康講座</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Seminar </span></strong>\r\n\r\n密西根中華婦女會將於四月十日舉辦<strong>健康講座</strong>，時間是下午5:00-7:30，地點為West Bloomfield 圖書館會議廳。健康講座是免費入場並提供披薩晚餐。\r\n\r\n密西根州社區健康部疾病防治中心 (DHWDC) 專門負責少數族群健康部門，訂定四月份為「少數族群月」，因之提供款項資助少數族群開辦活動，目的在促進少數族群對健保改革和(或) 推動學童在校營養午餐有更詳盡的認知。<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根州東南亞裔中心</span> (Asia Center-SE MI) 於今年一月申請專款辦理對健保改革認知活動，並於二月份獲選。該款項將可提供兩項主要活動：一為在四月二日為各個協辦單位所舉辦的訓練會，另一則是舉辦四場說明會，盼能將健保改革的訊息傳遞到各不同族群的角落。\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根中華婦女會</span>是<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根州東南亞裔中心</span>辦理此活動的協辦單位之一。四月十日當天的健康講座上，<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根州東南亞裔中心</span>主任既負責人<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">楊</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">芷雯</span>(Janilla Lee )博士將擔任主講人。<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">楊</span>博士 曾在福特汽車公司擔任高階主管。退休後到<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根大會</span>研習亞裔美人 (Asian American) 健康。她從1996 年起開始關心健康問題並對此問題始終不遺餘力的努力。此次活動經費既<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">楊</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">芷雯</span>博士申請來的。四月十日她將針對<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">歐巴馬</span>總統所提出的「健保改革案」對少數族群的影響，做深入的解釋。\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根中華婦女會</span>在四月十日活動中也將邀請<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">王鴻烈</span>牙醫博士及<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">林妙娟</span>牙醫博士賢伉儷為與會人士講解 「如何做好牙齒的健康保健和復健」。<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">王鴻烈</span>博士目前是密西根大學牙周病研究所所長，也是牙周病和植牙權威且經常在世界各地發表演講。<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">林妙娟</span>牙醫博士，畢業於<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根大學</span>，已行醫 十七年，目前在勒佛尼亞 (Livonia) 開設牙醫診所。\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根中華婦女會</span>於四月十日舉辦的健康講座內容與我們生活有直接的關係，所邀請到的主講人也都是在該專業中的頂尖代表人物，屆時必能提供最佳資訊，希望大家能踴躍出席。場地有限, 有意參加者，請與活動負責人報名:  傅曼玲 (248-705-6334) 侯珞怡 (248-788-7934) 韓燕如 (248-788-4669) 王禎楣 (248-641-7761)。','MCS Newsletter - 3/26/2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-3262011','','','2011-03-23 23:31:38','2011-03-24 03:31:38','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=138',0,'post','',0),(139,1,'2011-03-23 23:30:42','2011-03-24 03:30:42','','MCS Newsletter - 3/26/2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','138-revision','','','2011-03-23 23:30:42','2011-03-24 03:30:42','',138,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=139',0,'revision','',0),(140,1,'2011-03-30 22:35:28','2011-03-31 02:35:28','MCS Newsletter                              April 2, 2011\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Michigan</strong><strong> Chinese School</strong><strong> will have regular class on 4/2/2011 and 4/9/2011</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\r\n\r\nPlease  mark your calendar, MCS speech contest is scheduled on Saturday  4/9/2011. The top three place students will have the chance to attend  Interschool Speech Contest on 5/7/2011 which is hosted by our school.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">4/2/2011 Seminar : </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">獎助學金的爭取</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">和</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">教育基金的選</span></strong>\r\n\r\n時間：1:40pm -2:50pm, Saturday, April 2, 2011\r\n\r\n地點：Parents Lounge Room 2423,\r\n\r\n講題：(1)教育基金的選擇 - 劉健，Metlife 市場開發經理\r\n\r\n(2) 獎助學金的爭取 - 施安恂, Domino 教育咨詢公司高級顧問\r\n多米諾教育咨詢公司 - 風格獨特，全方位的教育指導\r\n潛心研究美國教育二十年的施安恂先生1985年到美國留學, 教育經驗豐富,\r\n僅用四年即培養出了羅茲（德）學者（Rhodes Scholar）及美國頂尖名校\r\n霍普金斯大學董事（Trustee）施文。\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">排骨便當</span></strong>\r\n\r\nChinchen Huang(黃勤珍) will have 排骨便當 for sale this weekend.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">4/10/2011健康講座</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Seminar  - see attached flyer </span></strong>\r\n\r\n密西根中華婦女會將於四月十日舉辦<strong>健康講座</strong>，時間是下午5:00-7:30，地點為West Bloomfield 圖書館會議廳。健康講座是免費入場並提供披薩晚餐。\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根中華婦女會</span>是<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根州東南亞裔中心</span>辦理此活動的協辦單位之一。四月十日當天的健康講座上，<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根州東南亞裔中心</span>主任既負責人<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">楊</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">芷雯</span>(Janilla Lee )博士將擔任主講人。<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">楊</span>博士 曾在福特汽車公司擔任高階主管。退休後到<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根大會</span>研習亞裔美人 (Asian American) 健康。她從1996 年起開始關心健康問題並對此問題始終不遺餘力的努力。此次活動經費既<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">楊</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">芷雯</span>博士申請來的。四月十日她將針對<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">歐巴馬</span>總統所提出的「健保改革案」對少數族群的影響，做深入的解釋。\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根中華婦女會</span>在四月十日活動中也將邀請<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">王鴻烈</span>牙醫博士及<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">林妙娟</span>牙醫博士賢伉儷為與會人士講解 「如何做好牙齒的健康保健和復健」。<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">王鴻烈</span>博士目前是密西根大學牙周病研究所所長，也是牙周病和植牙權威且經常在世界各地發表演講。<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">林妙娟</span>牙醫博士，畢業於<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根大學</span>，已行醫 十七年，目前在勒佛尼亞 (Livonia) 開設牙醫診所。\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">密西根中華婦女會</span>於四月十日舉辦的健康講座內容與我們生活有直接的關係，所邀請到的主講人也都是在該專業中的頂尖代表人物，屆時必能提供最佳資訊，希望大家能踴躍出席。場地有限, 有意參加者，請與活動負責人報名:  傅曼玲 (248-705-6334) 侯珞怡 (248-788-7934) 韓燕如 (248-788-4669) 王禎楣 (248-641-7761)。','MCS Newsletter - 4/2/2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-422011','','','2011-03-30 22:35:28','2011-03-31 02:35:28','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=140',0,'post','',0),(141,1,'2011-03-30 22:35:06','2011-03-31 02:35:06','','MCS Newsletter - 4/2/2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','140-revision','','','2011-03-30 22:35:06','2011-03-31 02:35:06','',140,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=141',0,'revision','',0);
